{"type":"text","timestamp":1778611646561,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","part":{"id":"prt_e1d83efd20011pkgmm0YMCSt5L","messageID":"msg_e1d8391d3001uBVYboA939jz6L","sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","type":"text","text":"Creating the hypothesis file now. The change is intentionally limited to `rtl/if_stage.sv` and only removes unnecessary reset plumbing from replay-table payload flops; `replay_valid` remains reset-gated so stale entries cannot be used.","time":{"start":1778611646418,"end":1778611646560},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0daaa9dcd3256f78016a0375be4dc48199b35447a3b8c3ed34","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778611659407,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_q2C7YbD7SERW1btegDyeb1yt","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\n+title: \"Resetless IF replay payloads\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest winning change added an 8-entry instruction replay table in IF,\n+  which improved CoreMark cycles under random instruction stalls but also added\n+  hundreds of resettable tag/instruction payload flops to a stage that is already\n+  sensitive to routing and control fanout. Earlier micro-opt wins came from\n+  pruning dead control and unnecessary reset muxing, and the replay table only\n+  needs deterministic validity after reset, not deterministic payload contents.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the accepted-fetch-only replay behavior exactly as-is, but reset only the\n+  replay_valid bits. Leave replay_tag and replay_instr payload registers\n+  resetless because they are architecturally ignored whenever their valid bit is\n+  clear and fully overwritten before any replay hit can occur.\n+\n+  This should trim synchronous reset muxing and reset-tree fanout introduced by\n+  the replay predictor without adding new prediction metadata, bypassing, or PC\n+  muxing. IPC should remain unchanged, while median Tang Nano 20K Fmax may rise\n+  modestly from lower IF-stage routing pressure.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Reset only replay_valid and the PC; leave replay_tag and replay_instr payload arrays resetless while preserving fill-on-imem-ready and replay-hit gating.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonett