{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778611677228,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_UCRRcWPve6Juj10f2kmhbJgJ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\n2: title: \"Resetless IF replay payloads\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The latest winning change added an 8-entry instruction replay table in IF,\n6:   which improved CoreMark cycles under random instruction stalls but also added\n7:   hundreds of resettable tag/instruction payload flops to a stage that is already\n8:   sensitive to routing and control fanout. Earlier micro-opt wins came from\n9:   pruning dead control and unnecessary reset muxing, and the replay table only\n10:   needs deterministic validity after reset, not deterministic payload contents.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Keep the accepted-fetch-only replay behavior exactly as-is, but reset only the\n13:   replay_valid bits. Leave replay_tag and replay_instr payload registers\n14:   resetless because they are architecturally ignored whenever their valid bit is\n15:   clear and fully overwritten before any replay hit can occur.\n16: \n17:   This should trim synchronous reset muxing and reset-tree fanout introduced by\n18:   the replay predictor without adding new prediction metadata, bypassing, or PC\n19:   muxing. IPC should remain unchanged, while median Tang Nano 20K Fmax may rise\n20:   modestly from lower IF-stage routing pressure.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n23:   confidence: medium\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n26:     description: \"Reset only replay_valid and the PC; leave replay_tag and replay_instr payload arrays resetless while preserving fill-on-imem-ready and replay-hit gating.\"\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r11s0\ntitle: \"Resetless IF replay payloads\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The latest winning change added an 8-entry instruction replay table in IF,\n  which improved CoreMark cycles under random instruction stalls but also added\n  hundreds of resettable tag/instruction payload flops to a stage that is already\n  sensitive to routing and control fanout. Earlier micro-opt wins came from\n  pruning dead control and unnecessary reset muxing, and the replay table only\n  needs deterministic validity after reset, not deterministic payload contents.\nhypothesis: |\n  Keep the accepted-fetch-only replay behavior exactly as-is, but reset only the\n  replay_valid bits. Leave replay_tag and replay_instr payload registers\n  resetless because they are architecturally ignored whenever their valid bit is\n  clear and fully overwritten before any replay hit can occur.\n\n  This should trim synchronous reset muxing and reset-tree fanout introduced by\n  the replay predictor without adding new prediction metadata, bypassing, or PC\n  muxing. IPC should remain unchanged, while median Tang Nano 20K Fmax may rise\n  modestly from lower IF-stage routing pressure.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778611677218,"end":1778611677227}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dd9204e83d38d15016a0375dd07708199a27417534b88e560"}},"id":"prt_e1d8467f4001zdWjrENiK4gzhy","sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","messageID":"msg_e1d8423eb001It0vZpotAyzmv4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778611677263,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_eZvNuGMlcm8wxICTu9gv1jPu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n3:   \"type\": \"object\",\n4:   \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n5:   \"properties\": {\n6:     \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n7:     \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n8:     \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n9:     \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n10:     \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n11:     \"expected_impact\": {\n12:       \"type\": \"object\",\n13:       \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n14:       \"properties\": {\n15:         \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n16:         \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n17:       }\n18:     },\n19:     \"changes\": {\n20:       \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,\n21:       \"items\": {\n22:         \"type\": \"object\",\n23:         \"required\": [\"file\",\"description\"],\n24:         \"properties\": {\n25:           \"file\":        {\n26:             \"type\": \"string\",\n27:             \"description\": \"Must be under rtl/ (any extension) or be a test/test_*.py cocotb suite. Anything else is rejected by the runtime sandbox check.\",\n28:             \"pattern\": \"^(rtl/[^.].*|test/test_[^/]+\\\\.py)$\"\n29:           },\n30:           \"description\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n31:         }\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n    \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n    \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n    \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n        \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n      }\n    },\n    \"changes\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","time":{"start":1778611677260,"end":1778611677262}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dd9204e83d38d15016a0375dd07988199b00a6e59c44340a5"}},"id":"prt_e1d84682e001849QraXd5WKFKv","sessionID":"ses_1e27d1632ffeubFDkuemfYsV49","messageID":"msg_e1d8423eb001It0vZpotAyzmv4"}}
