{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612694448,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","part":{"id":"prt_e1d93ea0d001FBcb7QJv1TZbnm","messageID":"msg_e1d91fe12001k2dGxMs8sAv3ev","sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused `micro_opt` hypothesis to narrow the IF replay tag from `pc[31:5]` to the bits needed under the enforced 1 MiB instruction-memory bound, preserving the 8-entry replay behavior while cutting fetch-stage compare/register routing.","time":{"start":1778612693517,"end":1778612694447},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ca6d2d55e445ee7016a0379d553108190904e14cc36722395","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612883678,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","part":{"id":"prt_e1d96cf92001JScVibQP0MsefU","messageID":"msg_e1d91fe12001k2dGxMs8sAv3ev","sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single-file hypothesis that keeps the successful 8-entry replay behavior but trims each replay tag from `pc[31:5]` to the legal 1 MiB instruction-memory tag `pc[19:5]`, reducing IF compare/register routing without changing hit behavior for valid programs.","time":{"start":1778612883346,"end":1778612883676},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_060674410d3e8459016a037a9335408197b5d235f2eb4ce78c","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612901046,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_g6lsp9MRBR4Q4XxDWRiEeF2u","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Trim IF replay tags to memory range\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The 8-entry IF replay table is the current strongest cycle-side win, but the\n+  follow-up attempts show the table is sensitive to routing: resetless payloads\n+  and wider tables regressed, and the lesson points at compare/control cost\n+  rather than capacity. Each replay entry still stores and compares pc[31:5],\n+  even though valid instruction fetches for this benchmark contract are bounded\n+  to the 1 MiB memory window.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the accepted-fetch-only 8-entry replay table and its exact ready/hit\n+  semantics, but shrink replay_tag from pc[31:5] to pc[19:5]. Together with the\n+  existing pc[4:2] index, those bits uniquely identify every word-aligned fetch\n+  address in the legal [0x00000000, 0x00100000) instruction-memory region, so\n+  CoreMark hit behavior and correctness for in-bounds execution are unchanged.\n+\n+  This removes 96 replay-tag flops and cuts each replay-hit comparator from 27\n+  bits to 15 bits, directly attacking the IF-stage compare/routing pressure that\n+  likely limited the replay-table follow-ups. Formal keeps imemReady high, and\n+  out-of-range PCs already violate the memory-bounds invariant rather than\n+  relying on replay tags for recovery.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Store and compare only replay_tag=pc[19:5] while preserving the 8-entry pc[4:2] index, fill-on-ready behavior, replay-on-stall hit semantics, and NRET=1 top-level contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Trim IF replay tags to memory range\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The 8-entry IF replay table is the current strongest cycle-side win, but the\n+  follow-up attempts show the table is sensitive to routing: resetless payloads\n+  and wider tables regressed, and the lesson points at compare/control cost\n+  rather than capacity. Each replay entry still stores and compares pc[31:5],\n+  even though valid instruction fetches for this benchmark contract are bounded\n+  to the 1 MiB memory window.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the accepted-fetch-only 8-entry replay table and its exact ready/hit\n+  semantics, but shrink replay_tag from pc[31:5] to pc[19:5]. Together with the\n+  existing pc[4:2] index, those bits uniquely identify every word-aligned fetch\n+  address in the legal [0x00000000, 0x00100000) instruction-memory region, so\n+  CoreMark hit behavior and correctness for in-bounds execution are unchanged.\n+\n+  This removes 96 replay-tag flops and cuts each replay-hit comparator from 27\n+  bits to 15 bits, directly attacking the IF-stage compare/routing pressure that\n+  likely limited the replay-table follow-ups. Formal keeps imemReady high, and\n+  out-of-range PCs already violate the memory-bounds invariant rather than\n+  relying on replay tags for recovery.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Store and compare only replay_tag=pc[19:5] while preserving the 8-entry pc[4:2] index, fill-on-ready behavior, replay-on-stall hit semantics, and NRET=1 top-level contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Trim IF replay tags to memory range\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The 8-entry IF replay table is the current strongest cycle-side win, but the\n+  follow-up attempts show the table is sensitive to routing: resetless payloads\n+  and wider tables regressed, and the lesson points at compare/control cost\n+  rather than capacity. Each replay entry still stores and compares pc[31:5],\n+  even though valid instruction fetches for this benchmark contract are bounded\n+  to the 1 MiB memory window.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the accepted-fetch-only 8-entry replay table and its exact ready/hit\n+  semantics, but shrink replay_tag from pc[31:5] to pc[19:5]. Together with the\n+  existing pc[4:2] index, those bits uniquely identify every word-aligned fetch\n+  address in the legal [0x00000000, 0x00100000) instruction-memory region, so\n+  CoreMark hit behavior and correctness for in-bounds execution are unchanged.\n+\n+  This removes 96 replay-tag flops and cuts each replay-hit comparator from 27\n+  bits to 15 bits, directly attacking the IF-stage compare/routing pressure that\n+  likely limited the replay-table follow-ups. Formal keeps imemReady high, and\n+  out-of-range PCs already violate the memory-bounds invariant rather than\n+  relying on replay tags for recovery.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Store and compare only replay_tag=pc[19:5] while preserving the 8-entry pc[4:2] index, fill-on-ready behavior, replay-on-stall hit semantics, and NRET=1 top-level contract.\"\n","additions":28,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778612901041,"end":1778612901045}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_060674410d3e8459016a037a93973c819793a44935d6f502e2"}},"id":"prt_e1d96d0de0017gS1ueMT79P4xs","sessionID":"ses_1e26f75b3ffeVj9RbJ4kTWRht5","messageID":"msg_e1d91fe12001k2dGxMs8sAv3ev"}}
