"motivation\": \"The only predictor that improved this bench core was the tiny instruction-fetch replay table, which converts random hot-loop iStall cycles into useful decoded instructions without branch target prediction or EX repair metadata. Follow-up attempts to widen the table or remove payload resets regressed, suggesting the remaining replay cost is tag/control routing rather than capacity or reset muxing.\\n\\nA predictor refinement should therefore keep the accepted-fetch-only replay semantics but reduce the fetch-stage compare and tag storage pressure that now sits on every stalled fetch decision.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Repack the current 8-entry single-word replay table into four two-word replay lines. Each line stores one full PC tag, two instruction words, and per-word valid bits; accepted fetches fill only the addressed half, clearing the sibling valid bit when a different tag replaces the line. On io_imemReady=0, a replay hit still requires a full tag match plus the selected half valid bit, then supplies the cached immutable instruction and asserts imem_effective_ready exactly as today.\\n\\nThis preserves the successful no-branch-prediction replay model and the NRET=1 RVFI contract while halving the number of stored tags and tag-select ro...","metadata":{"matches":36,"truncated":false},"title":"forward|load-use|rs1|rs2|regfile|decoder|immediate|NOP|hazard|CoreMark","time":{"start":1778614279027,"end":1778614279041}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0549321f9ad846a9016a038006cf6481959766bd53f56a90bc"}},"id":"prt_e1dac1b15001huowBQWjfqcJsK","sessionID":"ses_1e254750effeSqkX9XigYVbMht","messageID":"msg_e1dabe0dd001u03lBtqnAzFP6a"}}
