{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778614537976,"sessionID":"ses_1e254750effeSqkX9XigYVbMht","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_rxv0gpMrG4WFS9i2reU9f4V5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Mask false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both raw\n+  source fields of the following instruction, even when the following opcode\n+  does not consume rs2 or does not consume any register source. That creates\n+  occasional one-cycle bubbles after loads for OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR, LUI, AUIPC,\n+  JAL, FENCE, and other non-rs2 consumers whenever immediate bits alias the\n+  load rd. Prior lessons show added bypass datapaths often cost too much, so\n+  the safest remaining IPC micro-opt is to remove only false stalls without\n+  adding a new data path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small conservative source-use predecode to the hazard unit and gate the\n+  load-use comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2. R-type, branches, and stores\n+  keep both-source behavior, so a load feeding store data still stalls exactly\n+  as it does today; OP-IMM, LOAD, and JALR only check rs1; LUI, AUIPC, JAL, and\n+  FENCE check neither. Unknown or potentially source-reading encodings should\n+  default to conservative checking so illegal-instruction RVFI source reporting\n+  and trap behavior are not weakened.\n+\n+  This differs from the failed late load-store bypass attempt by not adding a\n+  MEM-stage store-data mux or changing forwarding. It should recover a modest\n+  number of CoreMark bubbles with only a small opcode decode in the existing\n+  hazard path, preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, memory ordering, and all\n+  architectural side-effect timing.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode the IF/ID opcode into conservative uses_rs1/uses_rs2 masks and apply those masks to the load-use rd comparisons.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction or opcode into the hazard unit while keeping the existing NRET=1 top-level IO unchanged.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Mask false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a load destination against both raw\n+  source fields of the following instruction, even when the following opcode\n+  does not consume rs2 or does not consume any register source. That creates\n+  occasional one-cycle bubbles after loads for OP-IMM, LOAD, JALR, LUI, AUIPC,\n+  JAL, FENCE, and other non-rs2 consumers whenever immediate bits alias the\n+  load rd. Prior lessons show added bypass datapaths often cost too much, so\n+  the safest remaining IPC micro-opt is to remove only false stalls without\n+  adding a new data path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small conservative source-use predecode to the hazard unit and gate the\n+  load-use comparisons with uses_rs1 and uses_rs2. R-type, branches, and stores\n+  keep both-source behavior, so a load feeding store data still stalls exactly\n+  as it does today; OP-IMM, LOAD, and JALR only check rs1; LUI, AUIPC, JAL, and\n+  FENCE check neither. Unknown or potentially source-reading encodings should\n+  default to conservative checking so illegal-instruction RVFI source reporting\n+  and trap behavior are not weakened.\n+\n+  This differs from the failed late load-store bypass attempt by not adding a\n+  MEM-stage store-data mux or changing forwarding. It should recover a modest\n+  number of CoreMark bubbles with only a small opcode decode in the existing\n+  hazard path, preserving the NRET=1 RVFI contract, memory ordering, and all\n+  architectural side-effect timing.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode the IF/ID opcode into conservative uses_rs1/uses_rs2 masks and apply those masks to the load-use rd comparisons.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction or opcode into the hazard unit while keeping the existing NRET=1 top-level IO unchanged.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r13s0\n+title: \"Mask false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use interlock compares a 