{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778615895835,"sessionID":"ses_1e23d079bffeuSJQ2dbzbV0CwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_APt8sbj33paXyOL4QZJPSUhe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r14s0\n2: title: \"Simplify IF replay muxing\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The accepted-fetch IF replay table is the current best cycle-side improvement,\n6:   but later replay follow-ups regressed when they added capacity, training logic,\n7:   or extra redirect filtering. The remaining promising micro-opt is therefore to\n8:   keep the exact replay behavior while reducing the mux and compare pressure that\n9:   now sits on the fetch-to-decode path.\n10: hypothesis: |\n11:   Refactor rtl/if_stage.sv so the replay tag compare only decides whether a\n12:   stalled fetch is usable, while the instruction-data mux selects directly between\n13:   live imem_data when io_imemReady is high and the indexed replay word when it is\n14:   low. On a miss with io_imemReady low, the existing imem_stall/flush path still\n15:   forces a NOP, so stale replay data is never decoded.\n16: \n17:   This should preserve the successful 8-entry accepted-fetch replay semantics,\n18:   reset behavior, redirect priority, RVFI-visible instruction stream, and NRET=1\n19:   contract, but remove one replay_hit-controlled 32-bit mux level from the common\n20:   IF instruction path. Also drop redundant redirect selection from the sequential\n21:   pc+4 increment term if it remains syntactically present, because redirect is\n22:   already handled by the priority PC update branch.\n23: expected_impact:\n24:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n25:   confidence: medium\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Factor replay_match/replay_hit from fetch_instr selection, use io_imemReady as the direct data mux select, and remove any redundant redirect muxing from the pc+4 increment path without changing fill-on-ready replay behavior.\"\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r14s0\ntitle: \"Simplify IF replay muxing\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The accepted-fetch IF replay table is the current best cycle-side improvement,\n  but later replay follow-ups regressed when they added capacity, training logic,\n  or extra redirect filtering. The remaining promising micro-opt is therefore to\n  keep the exact replay behavior while reducing the mux and compare pressure that\n  now sits on the fetch-to-decode path.\nhypothesis: |\n  Refactor rtl/if_stage.sv so the replay tag compare only decides whether a\n  stalled fetch is usable, while the instruction-data mux selects directly between\n  live imem_data when io_imemReady is high and the indexed replay word when it is\n  low. On a miss with io_imemReady low, the existing imem_stall/flush path still\n  forces a NOP, so stale replay data is never decoded.\n\n  This should preserve the successful 8-entry accepted-fetch replay semantics,\n  reset behavior, redirect priority, RVFI-visible instruction stream, and NRET=1\n  contract, but remove one replay_hit-controlled 32-bit mux level from the common\n  IF instruction path. Also drop redundant redirect selection from the sequential","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778615895830,"end":1778615895834}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bb306b4432b8762016a038657b66481909fd07845f18740ea"}},"id":"prt_e1dc4c706001RevubiRJkCfPXM","sessionID":"ses_1e23d079bffeuSJQ2dbzbV0CwL","messageID":"msg_e1dc4a28f001oS9CGY9lL1FHcF"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778615896002,"sessionID":"ses_1e23d079bffeuSJQ2dbzbV0CwL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DnNpe3RzPzqkjsqKbvsW81Sg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/schemas/hypothesis.schema.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n3:   \"type\": \"object\",\n4:   \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n5:   \"properties\": {\n6:     \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n7:     \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n8:     \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n9:     \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n10:     \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n11:     \"expected_impact\": {\n12:       \"type\": \"object\",\n13:       \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n14:       \"properties\": {\n15:         \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n16:         \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n17:       }\n18:     },\n19:     \"changes\": {\n20:       \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,\n21:       \"items\": {\n22:         \"type\": \"object\",\n23:         \"required\": [\"file\",\"description\"],\n24:         \"properties\": {\n25:           \"file\":        {\n26:             \"type\": \"string\",\n27:             \"description\": \"Must be under rtl/ (any extension) or be a test/test_*.py cocotb suite. Anything else is rejected by the runtime sandbox check.\",\n28:             \"pattern\": \"^(rtl/[^.].*|test/test_[^/]+\\\\.py)$\"\n29:           },\n30:           \"description\": {\"type\": \"string\"}\n31:         }\n32:       }\n33:     }\n34:   }\n35: }\n\n(End of file - total 35 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\",\n  \"type\": \"object\",\n  \"required\": [\"id\",\"title\",\"category\",\"motivation\",\"hypothesis\",\"expected_impact\",\"changes\"],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"id\":       {\"type\": \"string\", \"pattern\": \"^hyp-[0-9]{8}-[0-9]{3}(-r[0-9]+s[0-9]+)?$\"},\n    \"title\":    {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 5},\n    \"category\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"micro_opt\",\"structural\",\"extension\",\"predictor\",\"memory\"]},\n    \"motivation\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"hypothesis\":  {\"type\": \"string\", \"minLength\": 20},\n    \"expected_impact\": {\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"required\": [\"fitness_delta_pct\",\"confidence\"],\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"fitness_delta_pct\": {\"type\": \"integer\"},\n        \"confidence\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"enum\": [\"low\",\"medium\",\"high\"]}\n      }\n    },\n    \"changes\": {\n      \"type\": \"array\", \"minItems\": 1,","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"schemas/hypothesis.schema.json","time":{"start":1778615895995,"end":1778615896001}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bb306b4432b8762016a038657b6748190a94045cd43365a9b"}},"id":"prt_e1dc4c716002nTanwZhxQlLOlG","sessionID":"ses_1e23d079bffeuSJQ2dbzbV0CwL","messageID":"msg_e1dc4a28f001oS9CGY9lL1FHcF"}}
