{"type":"text","timestamp":1778616632683,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","part":{"id":"prt_e1dd003fc001zdqCuOQhb4cmXV","messageID":"msg_e1dce6937001FP1vfe27Lo4Eh0","sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","type":"text","text":"The most defensible `micro_opt` angle is another control-pruning pass: keep the current replay and pipeline structure intact, but stop carrying simple funct3-derived control bits through stage registers when the instruction word is already carried for RVFI.","time":{"start":1778616632316,"end":1778616632681},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ac1bc42007c6d31016a0389382d34819ba5fd68edce7188a5","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616644423,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jregjB48eC3xsLcyhh8JGAjs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Derive funct3 controls locally\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\n+  pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\n+  when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\n+  several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\n+  though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\n+  Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\n+  flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\n+  branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\n+  width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\n+  the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\n+  through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\n+  funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\n+  needs to export these simple mirror controls.\n+\n+  This keeps the five-stage timing, accepted-fetch replay table, NRET=1 RVFI\n+  contract, trap semantics, memory alignment behavior, and CoreMark instruction\n+  count unchanged. If the current implementation is still limited by decode and\n+  pipeline-control routing, trimming these bits should modestly improve median\n+  Fmax without risking the cycle-count regressions seen from predictor, replay,\n+  multiplier, and bypass experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove branch_op, mem_width, mem_sext, and early mem_to_reg fields from ID/EX and EX/MEM control structs while preserving the MEM/WB load-result select.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop exporting redundant funct3-derived branch and memory width/sign controls, while keeping all legality checks and is_illegal defaults intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the narrowed decoded control struct and continue carrying the instruction word needed for local downstream derivation and RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use in.instr[14:12] for branch comparison selection instead of a carried branch_op control field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive memory width and load signedness from in.instr funct3 bits, and create MEM/WB mem_to_reg from the validated mem_read control.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Derive funct3 controls locally\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\n+  pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\n+  when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\n+  several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\n+  though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\n+  Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\n+  flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\n+  branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\n+  width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\n+  the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\n+  through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\n+  funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\n+  needs to export these simple mirror controls.\n+\n+  This keeps the five-stage timing, accepted-fetch replay table, NRET=1 RVFI\n+  contract, trap semantics, memory alignment behavior, and CoreMark instruction\n+  count unchanged. If the current implementation is still limited by decode and\n+  pipeline-control routing, trimming these bits should modestly improve median\n+  Fmax without risking the cycle-count regressions seen from predictor, replay,\n+  multiplier, and bypass experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove branch_op, mem_width, mem_sext, and early mem_to_reg fields from ID/EX and EX/MEM control structs while preserving the MEM/WB load-result select.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop exporting redundant funct3-derived branch and memory width/sign controls, while keeping all legality checks and is_illegal defaults intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the narrowed decoded control struct and continue carrying the instruction word needed for local downstream derivation and RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use in.instr[14:12] for branch comparison selection instead of a carried branch_op control field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive memory width and load signedness from in.instr funct3 bits, and create MEM/WB mem_to_reg from the validated mem_read control.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,40 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Derive funct3 controls locally\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\n+  pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\n+  when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\n+  several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\n+  though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\n+  Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\n+  flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\n+  branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\n+  width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\n+  the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\n+  through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\n+  funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\n+  needs to export these simple mirror controls.\n+\n+  This keeps the five-stage timing, accepted-fetch replay table, NRET=1 RVFI\n+  contract, trap semantics, memory alignment behavior, and CoreMark instruction\n+  count unchanged. If the current implementation is still limited by decode and\n+  pipeline-control routing, trimming these bits should modestly improve median\n+  Fmax without risking the cycle-count regressions seen from predictor, replay,\n+  multiplier, and bypass experiments.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove branch_op, mem_width, mem_sext, and early mem_to_reg fields from ID/EX and EX/MEM control structs while preserving the MEM/WB load-result select.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop exporting redundant funct3-derived branch and memory width/sign controls, while keeping all legality checks and is_illegal defaults intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the narrowed decoded control struct and continue carrying the instruction word needed for local downstream derivation and RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use in.instr[14:12] for branch comparison selection instead of a carried branch_op control field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive memory width and load signedness from in.instr funct3 bits, and create MEM/WB mem_to_reg from the validated mem_read control.\"\n","additions":40,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778616644419,"end":1778616644422}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ac1bc42007c6d31016a0389388fe4819b8dea4a3274408dee"}},"id":"prt_e1dd0056b001eCNe0hu6ax1uC9","sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","messageID":"msg_e1dce6937001FP1vfe27Lo4Eh0"}}
