{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616650761,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_vP2aQ6qAyfgREFkkw1YQXnFl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\n2: title: \"Derive funct3 controls locally\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\n6:   pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\n7:   when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\n8:   several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\n9:   though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\n10:   Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\n11:   flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\n14:   branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\n15:   width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\n16:   the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\n17:   through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\n18:   funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\n19:   needs to export these simple mirror controls.\n20: \n21:   This keeps the five-stage timing, accepted-fetch replay table, NRET=1 RVFI\n22:   contract, trap semantics, memory alignment behavior, and CoreMark instruction\n23:   count unchanged. If the current implementation is still limited by decode and\n24:   pipeline-control routing, trimming these bits should modestly improve median\n25:   Fmax without risking the cycle-count regressions seen from predictor, replay,\n26:   multiplier, and bypass experiments.\n27: expected_impact:\n28:   fitness_delta_pct: 2\n29:   confidence: medium\n30: changes:\n31:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n32:     description: \"Remove branch_op, mem_width, mem_sext, and early mem_to_reg fields from ID/EX and EX/MEM control structs while preserving the MEM/WB load-result select.\"\n33:   - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n34:     description: \"Stop exporting redundant funct3-derived branch and memory width/sign controls, while keeping all legality checks and is_illegal defaults intact.\"\n35:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n36:     description: \"Latch the narrowed decoded control struct and continue carrying the instruction word needed for local downstream derivation and RVFI.\"\n37:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n38:     description: \"Use in.instr[14:12] for branch comparison selection instead of a carried branch_op control field.\"\n39:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n40:     description: \"Derive memory width and load signedness from in.instr funct3 bits, and create MEM/WB mem_to_reg from the validated mem_read control.\"\n\n(End of file - total 40 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\ntitle: \"Derive funct3 controls locally\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\n  pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\n  when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\n  several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\n  though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\n  Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\n  flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\nhypothesis: |\n  Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\n  branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\n  width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\n  the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\n  through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\n  funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\n  needs to export these simple mirror controls.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778616650754,"end":1778616650760}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_04c1fbd72b974b17016a03894a37a0819aa61341c9a78a942f"}},"id":"prt_e1dd04a4a001cX8l7afK1LpXPR","sessionID":"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON","messageID":"msg_e1dd0339a001dyGuFbOG21B57E"}}
