{"type":"text","timestamp":1778594858744,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea6fcffeeNkGAU3ED6gP8Q","part":{"id":"prt_e1c83be46001r4A0gqnvJtgtPx","messageID":"msg_e1c81e74e002muCTmt78G5QgEy","sessionID":"ses_1e37ea6fcffeeNkGAU3ED6gP8Q","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused micro-opt hypothesis to move rare DIV/REM operations off the combinational ALU critical path while keeping MUL single-cycle for CoreMark throughput.","time":{"start":1778594856518,"end":1778594858741},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_046b09f863a8b204016a03342862fc8195b45f43cf5f82e7a2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594880024,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea6fcffeeNkGAU3ED6gP8Q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_fxIakIrBcBfYyeSyY2h4gXvw","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Iterative divider off ALU critical path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU implements RV32IM DIV/REM with combinational / and % operators\n+  in the same execute-stage result mux as the common integer and multiply ops.\n+  CoreMark is dominated by adds, branches, loads, stores, and multiplies; rare\n+  division hardware can still cap FPGA Fmax and consume LUTs even when it is not\n+  on the dynamic hot path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace only DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with a small iterative divider/rem unit and\n+  stall the single-issue pipeline while that unit is busy. Keep ADD/SUB/logic,\n+  shifts, compares, address generation, branches, jumps, and all MUL/MULH\n+  variants single-cycle. This trades latency on rare divide instructions for a\n+  shorter EX-stage combinational path and lower LUT pressure, which should raise\n+  median Tang Nano 20K Fmax without materially changing CoreMark cycles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real combinational DIV/REM/% paths from the ALU while preserving ALTOPS behavior and single-cycle non-divide operations.\"\n+  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a sequential RV32M-correct divider/remainder unit covering signed, unsigned, divide-by-zero, and INT_MIN/-1 semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Start the divider for DIV/REM ops, hold the instruction until completion, and latch the final quotient or remainder into EX/MEM.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-busy stall input so IF, ID, and retirement remain ordered while a divide operation is in progress.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the execute-stage busy signal into the existing stall network without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Update or extend RV32M tests so divider/rem semantics remain covered after moving divide operations out of the combinational ALU.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\n+title: \"Iterative divider off ALU critical path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU implements RV32IM DIV/REM with combinational / and % operators\n+  in the same execute-stage result mux as the common integer and multiply ops.\n+  CoreMark is dominated by adds, branches, loads, stores, and multiplies; rare\n+  division hardware can still cap FPGA Fmax and consume LUTs even when it is not\n+  on the dynamic hot path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace only DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with a small iterative divider/rem unit and\n+  stall the single-issue pipeline while that unit is busy. Keep ADD/SUB/logic,\n+  shifts, compares, address generation, branches, jumps, and all MUL/MULH\n+  variants single-cycle. This trades latency on rare divide instructions for a\n+  shorter EX-stage combinational path and lower LUT pressure, which should raise\n+  median Tang Nano 20K Fmax without materially changing CoreMark cycles.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real combinational DIV/REM/% paths from the ALU while preserving ALTOPS behavior and single-cycle non-divide operations.\"\n+  - file: rtl/div_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a sequential RV32M-correct divider/remainder unit covering signed, unsigned, divide-by-zero, and INT_MIN/-1 semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Start the divider for DIV/REM ops, hold the instruction until completion, and latch the final quotient or remainder into EX/MEM.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-busy stall input so IF, ID, and retirement remain ordered while a divide operation is in progress.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the execute-stage busy signal into the existing stall network without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Update or extend RV32M tests so divider/rem semantics remain covered after moving divide operations out of the combinational ALU.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260