{"type":"text","timestamp":1778596612181,"sessionID":"ses_1e3640324ffe29MRVC4OP450Eq","part":{"id":"prt_e1c9e87e9001xCRQDWA4b2fGfb","messageID":"msg_e1c9e2bf7001k7GRRZvm6jGsE5","sessionID":"ses_1e3640324ffe29MRVC4OP450Eq","type":"text","text":"The strongest micro-optimization angle is the remaining ALU multiplier cost: the current ALU builds three independent 64-bit products every cycle, so sharing that into one sign-controlled product should reduce routing/resource pressure without adding stalls.","time":{"start":1778596612073,"end":1778596612180},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e41a556ffddbbac016a033b03fa2481968e9d56778b880f47","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596626266,"sessionID":"ses_1e3640324ffe29MRVC4OP450Eq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_dusv5P5LTL8VcqUqCkl9Ppk0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Share RV32M multiplier datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  After moving DIV/REM out of the combinational ALU, the remaining RV32M\n+  multiplier logic is a likely Fmax and routing limiter. The current ALU\n+  computes signed*signed, unsigned*unsigned, and signed*unsigned 64-bit\n+  products in parallel even though each instruction consumes only one result.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the three parallel product nets with a single sign-controlled\n+  extended multiply selected from the ALU_MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU operation.\n+  MUL can still use the low 32 bits, while the high-half variants select the\n+  correct signedness through operand extension. This should reduce LUT/DSP\n+  duplication and the ALU result-mux/routing cone without changing pipeline\n+  latency, CoreMark instruction count, RVFI behavior, or ALTOPS semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Collapse the three RV32M multiply products into one sign-selected extended product while preserving ALTOPS substitutions and single-cycle MUL latency.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Keep or extend MULH/MULHU/MULHSU edge-case vectors to guard signedness correctness after sharing the multiplier datapath.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Share RV32M multiplier datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  After moving DIV/REM out of the combinational ALU, the remaining RV32M\n+  multiplier logic is a likely Fmax and routing limiter. The current ALU\n+  computes signed*signed, unsigned*unsigned, and signed*unsigned 64-bit\n+  products in parallel even though each instruction consumes only one result.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the three parallel product nets with a single sign-controlled\n+  extended multiply selected from the ALU_MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU operation.\n+  MUL can still use the low 32 bits, while the high-half variants select the\n+  correct signedness through operand extension. This should reduce LUT/DSP\n+  duplication and the ALU result-mux/routing cone without changing pipeline\n+  latency, CoreMark instruction count, RVFI behavior, or ALTOPS semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Collapse the three RV32M multiply products into one sign-selected extended product while preserving ALTOPS substitutions and single-cycle MUL latency.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Keep or extend MULH/MULHU/MULHSU edge-case vectors to guard signedness correctness after sharing the multiplier datapath.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-2