{"type":"text","timestamp":1778598686152,"sessionID":"ses_1e3449616ffeVvcV2sf2paayyX","part":{"id":"prt_e1cbe2482001iMrkximAaSq6Cu","messageID":"msg_e1cbbac42002CZUjPkWMZF9OAf","sessionID":"ses_1e3449616ffeVvcV2sf2paayyX","type":"text","text":"The strongest untried `micro_opt` angle is cycle recovery rather than more EX datapath surgery: avoid conservative load-use bubbles when the following store only needs the loaded value as store data, then forward that value late in MEM so RVFI and dmem see the correct source data.","time":{"start":1778598683778,"end":1778598686150},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07953af02997b2fc016a03431b82f88195b833bcad6a31e158","phase":"commentary"}}}}
