{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598733409,"sessionID":"ses_1e3449616ffeVvcV2sf2paayyX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Udej5kijqaT7qBRGSnkMUbUg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Late load-store data bypass\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use detector stalls whenever a load in EX has an rd\n+  matching either raw source field of the following IF/ID instruction. That is\n+  necessary for ALU operands, branch compares, and store address bases, but it\n+  is over-conservative for a STORE whose rs2 data is not consumed until MEM.\n+  CoreMark's timed kernels perform many load/store moves and immediate-form\n+  operations, so avoidable one-cycle bubbles directly reduce iterations per\n+  cycle without helping correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refine the load-use hazard to distinguish operands needed in EX from store\n+  data that can be supplied one stage later. For a following STORE, keep the\n+  stall only when the load feeds rs1, the address base; allow an rs2-only\n+  dependency to advance and resolve it with a MEM-stage bypass from the current\n+  MEM/WB result into the store-data path. The bypass must also update the\n+  retiring store's RVFI rs2_rdata and mem_wdata fields so formal/cosim observe\n+  the architectural source value.\n+\n+  Default unknown or illegal encodings to conservative source use in the\n+  hazard predecode, preserving trap and RVFI behavior. This should recover IPC\n+  from load-to-store and false rs2-immediate hazards while adding only a small\n+  MEM data mux, avoiding the fetch critical-path costs seen in prior predictor\n+  attempts and the EX multiplier regressions from prior micro-opts.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify load-use stalls by whether the following instruction needs each source in EX; treat STORE rs2 as late-consumable and unknown/illegal encodings conservatively.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM/WB-to-store-data bypass for rs2-only load-store dependencies and use the forwarded value for dmem_wdata, RVFI mem_wdata, and RVFI rs2_rdata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction metadata needed by the refined hazard logic while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_load_store_forward.py\n+    description: \"Add a focused cocotb regression for load-to-store data forwarding and for immediate-form instructions that should not trigger false rs2 load-use stalls.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Late load-store data bypass\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current load-use detector stalls whenever a load in EX has an rd\n+  matching either raw source field of the following IF/ID instruction. That is\n+  necessary for ALU operands, branch compares, and store address bases, but it\n+  is over-conservative for a STORE whose rs2 data is not consumed until MEM.\n+  CoreMark's timed kernels perform many load/store moves and immediate-form\n+  operations, so avoidable one-cycle bubbles directly reduce iterations per\n+  cycle without helping correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refine the load-use hazard to distinguish operands needed in EX from store\n+  data that can be supplied one stage later. For a following STORE, keep the\n+  stall only when the load feeds rs1, the address base; allow an rs2-only\n+  dependency to advance and resolve it with a MEM-stage bypass from the current\n+  MEM/WB result into the store-data path. The bypass must also update the\n+  retiring store's RVFI rs2_rdata and mem_wdata fields so formal/cosim observe\n+  the architectural source value.\n+\n+  Default unknown or illegal encodings to conservative source use in the\n+  hazard predecode, preserving trap and RVFI behavior. This should recover IPC\n+  from load-to-store and false rs2-immediate hazards while adding only a small\n+  MEM data mux, avoiding the fetch critical-path costs seen in prior predictor\n+  attempts and the EX multiplier regressions from prior micro-opts.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify load-use stalls by whether the following instruction needs each source in EX; treat STORE rs2 as late-consumable and unknown/illegal encodings conservatively.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a MEM/WB-to-store-data bypass for rs2-only load-store dependencies and use the forwarded value for dmem_wdata, RVFI mem_wdata, and RVFI rs2_rdata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction metadata needed by the refined hazard logic while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_load_store_forward.py\n+    description: \"Add a focused cocotb regression for load-to-store data forwarding and for immediate-form instructions that should not trigger false rs2 load-use stalls.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/h