{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598750756,"sessionID":"ses_1e3449616ffeVvcV2sf2paayyX","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3jUBqT0NBr1Hhtzp7Gil65yE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r3s0\n2: title: \"Late load-store data bypass\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current load-use detector stalls whenever a load in EX has an rd\n6:   matching either raw source field of the following IF/ID instruction. That is\n7:   necessary for ALU operands, branch compares, and store address bases, but it\n8:   is over-conservative for a STORE whose rs2 data is not consumed until MEM.\n9:   CoreMark's timed kernels perform many load/store moves and immediate-form\n10:   operations, so avoidable one-cycle bubbles directly reduce iterations per\n11:   cycle without helping correctness.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Refine the load-use hazard to distinguish operands needed in EX from store\n14:   data that can be supplied one stage later. For a following STORE, keep the\n15:   stall only when the load feeds rs1, the address base; allow an rs2-only\n16:   dependency to advance and resolve it with a MEM-stage bypass from the current\n17:   MEM/WB result into the store-data path. The bypass must also update the\n18:   retiring store's RVFI rs2_rdata and mem_wdata fields so formal/cosim observe\n19:   the architectural source value.\n20: \n21:   Default unknown or illegal encodings to conservative source use in the\n22:   hazard predecode, preserving trap and RVFI behavior. This should recover IPC\n23:   from load-to-store and false rs2-immediate hazards while adding only a small\n24:   MEM data mux, avoiding the fetch critical-path costs seen in prior predictor\n25:   attempts and the EX multiplier regressions from prior micro-opts.\n26: expected_impact:\n27:   fitness_delta_pct: 4\n28:   confidence: medium\n29: changes:\n30:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n31:     description: \"Qualify load-use stalls by whether the following instruction needs each source in EX; treat STORE rs2 as late-consumable and unknown/illegal encodings conservatively.\"\n32:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n33:     description: \"Add a MEM/WB-to-store-data bypass for rs2-only load-store dependencies and use the forwarded value for dmem_wdata, RVFI mem_wdata, and RVFI rs2_rdata.\"\n34:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n35:     description: \"Pass the IF/ID instruction metadata needed by the refined hazard logic while preserving the nret=1 top-level RVFI port contract.\"\n36:   - file: test/test_load_store_forward.py\n37:     description: \"Add a focused cocotb regression for load-to-store data forwarding and for immediate-form instructions that should not trigger false rs2 load-use stalls.\"\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r3s0\ntitle: \"Late load-store data bypass\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current load-use detector stalls whenever a load in EX has an rd\n  matching either raw source field of the following IF/ID instruction. That is\n  necessary for ALU operands, branch compares, and store address bases, but it\n  is over-conservative for a STORE whose rs2 data is not consumed until MEM.\n  CoreMark's timed kernels perform many load/store moves and immediate-form\n  operations, so avoidable one-cycle bubbles directly reduce iterations per\n  cycle without helping correctness.\nhypothesis: |\n  Refine the load-use hazard to distinguish operands needed in EX from store\n  data that can be supplied one stage later. For a following STORE, keep the\n  stall only when the load feeds rs1, the address base; allow an rs2-only\n  dependency to advance and resolve it with a MEM-stage bypass from the current\n  MEM/WB result into the store-data path. The bypass must also update the\n  retiring store's RVFI rs2_rdata and mem_wdata fields so formal/cosim observe\n  the architectural source value.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778598750749,"end":1778598750755}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05f2c04eb9862fac016a03435b6e78819399b6e698f891ae56"}},"id":"prt_e1cbf1d93001vEEgedtZ1IqJ44","sessionID":"ses_1e3449616ffeVvcV2sf2paayyX","messageID":"msg_e1cbee6e8001nhA0pxLrqX8yot"}}
