{"type":"text","timestamp":1778600419493,"sessionID":"ses_1e327f88cffeOc9a2hwK26VZFa","part":{"id":"prt_e1cd8963b001gwrkVnLPnRonc4","messageID":"msg_e1cd871e10020B0ddlbcrItaw2","sessionID":"ses_1e327f88cffeOc9a2hwK26VZFa","type":"text","text":"Prior micro-opt results show the only strong win was removing divide from the ALU cone; multiplier sharing and load-use/store bypass both regressed. I’m going to propose a narrower Fmax-oriented micro-opt that removes dead control/data width from the hot forwarding path rather than adding new prediction or buffering state.","time":{"start":1778600416827,"end":1778600419493},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0223768eef7c8415016a0349e0b76881979d1bfb92268fefaf","phase":"commentary"}}}}
