{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778600703946,"sessionID":"ses_1e327f88cffeOc9a2hwK26VZFa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_UI7ruHyFSJTwVJhb13sGurZp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Iterative high-half multiply\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful divider change showed that removing rare RV32M operations from\n+  the common EX-stage combinational cone can raise FPGA Fmax without materially\n+  hurting CoreMark cycles. The current ALU still computes three 64-bit multiply\n+  products in parallel for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU, even though CoreMark's\n+  timed hot path is expected to use ordinary low-half MUL far more often than\n+  high-half multiply variants.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a single-cycle low-half multiply, but move MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU onto a small iterative high-half multiplier that reuses the existing\n+  execute-busy stall pattern. This should let synthesis reduce the common ALU\n+  multiplier to only the low 32 result bits for MUL, while removing the signed\n+  and signed/unsigned high-product cones from the normal ADD/branch/load/store\n+  execute path.\n+\n+  Unlike the prior shared 33x33 multiplier attempt, this does not add a wider\n+  signedness mux to every multiply operation. The latency penalty is paid only\n+  for high-half M-extension instructions, which should be rare or absent in the\n+  CoreMark timed region, while RV32M correctness remains covered by dedicated\n+  unit tests and cosim.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving ALTOPS substitutions and single-cycle low-half MUL.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mulh_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an iterative RV32M-correct high-half multiplier for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with explicit start/done/ack behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route high-half multiply ops through the new unit, hold ID/EX while it runs, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result on completion.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reuse the existing execute-busy pipeline freeze path for high-half multiply stalls without changing redirect or memory-stall priority.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain RV32M edge-case coverage by moving high-half multiply expectations to the new execution path or unit while keeping low-half MUL ALU vectors.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r4s0\n+title: \"Iterative high-half multiply\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful divider change showed that removing rare RV32M operations from\n+  the common EX-stage combinational cone can raise FPGA Fmax without materially\n+  hurting CoreMark cycles. The current ALU still computes three 64-bit multiply\n+  products in parallel for MUL, MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU, even though CoreMark's\n+  timed hot path is expected to use ordinary low-half MUL far more often than\n+  high-half multiply variants.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a single-cycle low-half multiply, but move MULH, MULHU, and\n+  MULHSU onto a small iterative high-half multiplier that reuses the existing\n+  execute-busy stall pattern. This should let synthesis reduce the common ALU\n+  multiplier to only the low 32 result bits for MUL, while removing the signed\n+  and signed/unsigned high-product cones from the normal ADD/branch/load/store\n+  execute path.\n+\n+  Unlike the prior shared 33x33 multiplier attempt, this does not add a wider\n+  signedness mux to every multiply operation. The latency penalty is paid only\n+  for high-half M-extension instructions, which should be rare or absent in the\n+  CoreMark timed region, while RV32M correctness remains covered by dedicated\n+  unit tests and cosim.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving ALTOPS substitutions and single-cycle low-half MUL.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mulh_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an iterative RV32M-correct high-half multiplier for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with explicit start/done/ack behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route high-half multiply ops through the new unit, hold ID/EX while it runs, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result on completion.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reuse the existing execute-busy pipeline freeze path for high-half multiply stalls without changing redirect or memory-stall priority.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Retain RV32M edge-case coverage by moving high-half multiply expectations to the new execution path or unit while keeping low-half MUL ALU vectors.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-ar