{"type":"text","timestamp":1778602436940,"sessionID":"ses_1e30c4a2affeTv5xwT1AGho4a5","part":{"id":"prt_e1cf76836001s0XMWc3d7Z7eV4","messageID":"msg_e1cf6b631001Szsg2GcPhC7FuP","sessionID":"ses_1e30c4a2affeTv5xwT1AGho4a5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a localized `mem_stage.sv` micro-optimization rather than another predictor, buffer, or multiplier split, because the prior history suggests additions to fetch/control or RV32M paths have not paid for their timing cost.","time":{"start":1778602436662,"end":1778602436940},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ca2098133ee0a9f016a0351c48a4c8193bf40f60bb80b7a1f","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778602452371,"sessionID":"ses_1e30c4a2affeTv5xwT1AGho4a5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_6EoBCmbRrBce5bv0NaGMDoBj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r5s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r5s0\n+title: \"Case-decoded load byte lanes\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest prior result came from shortening a real timing cone without\n+  adding new frontend or memory-ordering state. Recent predictor, store-buffer,\n+  and multiplier refinements all regressed because extra muxing and control\n+  pressure outweighed any cycle savings. The MEM stage still contains dynamic\n+  byte-lane shifts on the load/store path, including a variable right shift by\n+  addr[1:0] * 8, which can synthesize into a wider mux cone on the BRAM-read to\n+  MEM/WB path used heavily by CoreMark.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rewrite the MEM-stage byte/halfword load extraction and byte-mask generation\n+  as explicit small case trees on alu_result[1:0] and mem_width. This removes\n+  the variable shift and shift-amount multiply from the common load path while\n+  preserving the existing dmem port contract, misalignment trap gating, RVFI\n+  ALIGNED_MEM reporting, and single-cycle MEM latency. IPC should be unchanged,\n+  but LUT depth and routing on the load-data and store-mask cones should drop\n+  enough to modestly improve median Tang Nano 20K Fmax.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace dynamic byte-lane shifts and masks with explicit case-based byte/halfword selectors while preserving misalignment, dmem, and RVFI behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r5s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/benc