{"type":"text","timestamp":1778604071610,"sessionID":"ses_1e2f21b44ffejMycAl11cXQ1F9","part":{"id":"prt_e1d10532a001ih1ekMV8lwFp3E","messageID":"msg_e1d0f6b1d001m7fF8J4mr7TNj0","sessionID":"ses_1e2f21b44ffejMycAl11cXQ1F9","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a `micro_opt` hypothesis that targets Fmax by pruning unused pipeline control/state bits, keeping IPC unchanged and avoiding the previously-regressing predictor, multiplier, and memory-bypass paths.","time":{"start":1778604069674,"end":1778604071610},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0b66041994a7b4f3016a03582593448194bcf63d9c3277b6b2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778604092574,"sessionID":"ses_1e2f21b44ffejMycAl11cXQ1F9","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_PszM2K1OP8d6TdaTc0Rcu3ok","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline control bits\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench attempts regressed when they added new muxing or control to the\n+  already-shallow pipeline. The current RTL still carries several EX-only or\n+  unused control/state fields through later pipeline registers, including the\n+  redundant LUI control bit and unused branch metadata after EX has already\n+  resolved the redirect. Those flops and nets do not improve IPC, but they can\n+  add routing pressure and fanout on the FPGA implementation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Narrow the control/state carried past each stage to only what the next stages\n+  actually consume. Remove the unused is_lui control bit because LUI is already\n+  represented by ALU_LUI plus alu_src, stop storing branch_taken/branch_target\n+  in EX/MEM after redirect resolution, and explicitly avoid propagating EX-only\n+  decode controls into MEM/WB. This should reduce register count, fanout, and\n+  late-stage routing without changing retirement timing, RVFI contents, trap\n+  behavior, memory ordering, or CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused pipeline-bundle fields and narrow late-stage control state to the bits consumed after EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the redundant is_lui output while preserving ALU_LUI decode and illegal-instruction defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop wiring the removed LUI control bit and populate only the retained control fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Do not register unused branch metadata after redirect resolution, and pass only MEM/WB-relevant control state forward.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate only the control bits needed by WB and RVFI while preserving memory masks, misalignment traps, and load data.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline control bits\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench attempts regressed when they added new muxing or control to the\n+  already-shallow pipeline. The current RTL still carries several EX-only or\n+  unused control/state fields through later pipeline registers, including the\n+  redundant LUI control bit and unused branch metadata after EX has already\n+  resolved the redirect. Those flops and nets do not improve IPC, but they can\n+  add routing pressure and fanout on the FPGA implementation.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Narrow the control/state carried past each stage to only what the next stages\n+  actually consume. Remove the unused is_lui control bit because LUI is already\n+  represented by ALU_LUI plus alu_src, stop storing branch_taken/branch_target\n+  in EX/MEM after redirect resolution, and explicitly avoid propagating EX-only\n+  decode controls into MEM/WB. This should reduce register count, fanout, and\n+  late-stage routing without changing retirement timing, RVFI contents, trap\n+  behavior, memory ordering, or CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove unused pipeline-bundle fields and narrow late-stage control state to the bits consumed after EX.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the redundant is_lui output while preserving ALU_LUI decode and illegal-instruction defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop wiring the removed LUI control bit and populate only the retained control fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Do not register unused branch metadata after redirect resolution, and pass only MEM/WB-relevant control state forward.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate only the control bits needed by WB and RVFI while preserving memory masks, misalignment traps, and load data.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline control bits\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent bench attempts regressed when they added new muxing or control to the\n+