{"type":"text","timestamp":1778605606694,"sessionID":"ses_1e2de85a8ffeJTssrM0lEW0CPw","part":{"id":"prt_e1d27c0960015R1KVqkV0JgzDQ","messageID":"msg_e1d21faf3001GdpHO1YEOjjCW2","sessionID":"ses_1e2de85a8ffeJTssrM0lEW0CPw","type":"text","text":"The strongest micro-opt angle from the history is another no-new-control pruning pass: remove reset mux/fanout from wide pipeline payload flops while still resetting valid and side-effect controls so post-reset behavior remains precise.","time":{"start":1778605605014,"end":1778605606693},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07ff3dd8f8b3ea42016a035e24d5148196807cede4a8565f14","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778605628092,"sessionID":"ses_1e2de85a8ffeJTssrM0lEW0CPw","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_xwX11URA0WG4hpBN3hnJ8WuM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Valid-only pipeline payload resets\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest winning bench change improved fitness by pruning dead pipeline\n+  control state, which suggests this shallow FPGA core is sensitive to fanout,\n+  routing, and unnecessary flop-side muxing. The stage registers still\n+  synchronously clear wide PC, instruction, operand, immediate, memory, and RVFI\n+  payload fields on reset even though retirement and architectural side effects\n+  are controlled by valid and compact control bits.\n+\n+  Those reset muxes do not improve CoreMark IPC, but they can add high-fanout\n+  reset routing and extra logic on the same pipeline registers used by the hot\n+  execute, memory, forwarding, and writeback paths.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB pipeline registers to reset only the\n+  fields that can cause visible side effects or false hazards: valid bits,\n+  compact control bits, destination registers, and memory masks as needed.\n+  Leave wide payload fields such as pc, instr, operands, immediates, ALU result,\n+  load data, and RVFI data as don't-care while invalid, then load them normally\n+  when each stage captures a real instruction.\n+\n+  Keep the IF PC, register file, and divider state reset behavior unchanged.\n+  This should reduce synchronous reset muxing and reset-net pressure without\n+  adding prediction, buffering, extra stalls, or any cycle-level behavior\n+  change. RVFI remains precise because all retired instructions still carry\n+  fully assigned payload fields when valid is high.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Reset only ID/EX valid, compact control, and hazard-visible destination/source metadata while leaving wide payload fields unreset until captured.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Apply valid/control-only reset to EX/MEM, preserving dmem stall and divider hold behavior while clearing side-effect controls after reset.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Apply valid/control/mask-only reset to MEM/WB so wide RVFI and writeback payload fields avoid reset muxes but are fully assigned on valid retirements.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Valid-only pipeline payload resets\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest winning bench change improved fitness by pruning dead pipeline\n+  control state, which suggests this shallow FPGA core is sensitive to fanout,\n+  routing, and unnecessary flop-side muxing. The stage registers still\n+  synchronously clear wide PC, instruction, operand, immediate, memory, and RVFI\n+  payload fields on reset even though retirement and architectural side effects\n+  are controlled by valid and compact control bits.\n+\n+  Those reset muxes do not improve CoreMark IPC, but they can add high-fanout\n+  reset routing and extra logic on the same pipeline registers