{"type":"text","timestamp":1778607034793,"sessionID":"ses_1e2c4eb7dffefUcGsmRuq4oMSK","part":{"id":"prt_e1d3d8f5b001561v4i8pyLAZai","messageID":"msg_e1d3ca6cd001JiG8o555zWwbyf","sessionID":"ses_1e2c4eb7dffefUcGsmRuq4oMSK","type":"text","text":"The selected hypothesis is a minimal payload-pruning optimization: `ex_mem_t.write_data` duplicates the already carried post-forward `rs2_val`, so removing it should cut 32 EX/MEM flops/nets without adding new control logic.","time":{"start":1778607034203,"end":1778607034792},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06e85c37ba6193e3016a0363ba19488193aab77256c0ede7cf","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778607049257,"sessionID":"ses_1e2c4eb7dffefUcGsmRuq4oMSK","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_2mMJlnGb1yYOAWw5o8MEAr0x","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r8s0\n+title: \"Remove duplicate store-data payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The recent winning bench changes improved fitness by pruning dead control and reset plumbing rather than adding predictors or buffers. The current EX/MEM bundle still carries both write_data and rs2_val even though both are assigned the same post-forward rs2 operand and stay identical for stores, RVFI source reporting, and held divide completion.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Delete the redundant ex_mem_t.write_data field and use ex_mem_t.rs2_val as the single canonical post-forward store-data operand in MEM. This removes a 32-bit pipeline payload register and its routing from the EX/MEM boundary while preserving store byte replication, RVFI rs2_rdata, forwarding behavior, memory ordering, trap handling, and the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the duplicate write_data member from ex_mem_t and document rs2_val as the canonical post-forward store operand.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop assigning the removed EX/MEM write_data field; continue preserving the forwarded rs2 value in rs2_val for stores and RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive store byte replication from in.rs2_val instead of the removed write_data payload, preserving masks, misalignment gating, and RVFI mem_wdata.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r8s0\n+title: \"Remove duplicate store-data payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The recent winning bench changes improved fitness by pruning dead control and reset plumbing rather than adding predictors or buffers. The current EX/MEM bundle still carries both write_data and rs2_val even though both are assigned the same post-forward rs2 operand and stay identical for stores, RVFI source reporting, and held divide completion.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Delete the redundant ex_mem_t.write_data field and use ex_mem_t.rs2_val as the single canonical post-forward store-data operand in MEM. This removes a 32-bit pipeline payload register and its routing from the EX/MEM boundary while preserving store byte replication, RVFI rs2_rdata, forwarding behavior, memory ordering, trap handling, and the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the duplicate write_data member from ex_mem_t and document rs2_val as the canonical post-forward store operand.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop assigning the removed EX/MEM write_data field; continue preserving the forwarded rs2 value in rs2_val for stores and RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive store byte replication from in.rs2_val instead of the removed write_data payload, preserving masks, misalignment gating, and RVFI mem_wdata.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":