{"type":"text","timestamp":1778608948686,"sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c3d0ffetzkVJdQsXFZZ7F","part":{"id":"prt_e1d5ac06d001FcqUg2IR0dXV7T","messageID":"msg_e1d5a59f4001ujgU8M3rUXTApP","sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c3d0ffetzkVJdQsXFZZ7F","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis as a single-file EX-stage micro-opt so the implementation phase stays narrow and avoids the previously regressive predictor/memory/M-unit categories.","time":{"start":1778608947309,"end":1778608948683},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_05019092647891db016a036b3338848193a8f185fe4b9ff898","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778608965288,"sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c3d0ffetzkVJdQsXFZZ7F","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_a1z08G2a4WrI4aKZPwYdtQJR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Share EX add and compare cones\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench history shows the best improvements came from removing timing and\n+  routing pressure without adding new prediction, memory-ordering, or M-unit\n+  control. The current EX stage still spells out several equivalent 32-bit PC\n+  adders and branch comparisons in separate expressions that feed redirect,\n+  pc_next, JAL link writeback, and RVFI pc_wdata. Even if synthesis shares some\n+  of this logic, making the sharing explicit is a low-risk way to reduce the\n+  branch/redirect cone that CoreMark exercises heavily.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv to compute common EX address terms once: pc_plus4,\n+  pc_imm_sum, and jalr_target. Reuse those wires for branch_target,\n+  jump_target, JAL/JALR link data, pc_next, and redirect_target instead of\n+  repeating in.pc + 4 and in.pc + imm expressions.\n+\n+  At the same time, rewrite the branch comparator around shared eq,\n+  signed_lt, and unsigned_lt primitives, using inversion for BNE/BGE/BGEU\n+  rather than independent >= and != comparator expressions. This should trim\n+  LUT depth and fanout on the EX redirect path without changing instruction\n+  latency, stall behavior, RVFI ordering, trap semantics, or the NRET=1 port\n+  contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Factor repeated PC adders and branch comparisons into shared EX-stage wires while preserving redirect, link, pc_next, divide, and RVFI behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Share EX add and compare cones\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench history shows the best improvements came from removing timing and\n+  routing pressure without adding new prediction, memory-ordering, or M-unit\n+  control. The current EX stage still spells out several equivalent 32-bit PC\n+  adders and branch comparisons in separate expressions that feed redirect,\n+  pc_next, JAL link writeback, and RVFI pc_wdata. Even if synthesis shares some\n+  of this logic, making the sharing explicit is a low-risk way to reduce the\n+  branch/redirect cone that CoreMark exercises heavily.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Refactor rtl/ex_stage.sv to compute common EX address terms once: pc_plus4,\n+  pc_imm_sum, and jalr_target. Reuse those wires for branch_target,\n+  jump_target, JAL/JALR link data, pc_next, and redirect_target instead of\n+  repeating in.pc + 4 and in.pc + imm expressions.\n+\n+  At the same time, rewrite the branch comparator around shared eq,\n+  signed_lt, and unsigned_lt primitives, using inversion for BNE/BGE/BGEU\n+  rather than independent >= and != comparator expressions. This should trim\n+  LUT depth and fanout on the EX redirect path without changing instruction\n+  latency, stall behavior, RVFI ordering, trap semantics, or the NRET=1 port\n+  contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_p