{"type":"text","timestamp":1778611740562,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d16acffeo0Xe6gwD6BKluF","part":{"id":"prt_e1d8556c3001v5DdKbmx7xMC2C","messageID":"msg_e1d840c9f001yVpCcIpVQKs2GQ","sessionID":"ses_1e27d16acffeo0Xe6gwD6BKluF","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a capacity/implementation refactor of the winning replay-table mechanism: keep it direct-mapped and metadata-free, but make tag/data storage resetless and expand from 8 to 16 entries to reduce hot-loop iStall conflict misses.","time":{"start":1778611738307,"end":1778611740561},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ee6fcfaaafbd987016a03761a31108195a66790bbb87fa8d8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778611759731,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d16acffeo0Xe6gwD6BKluF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_WCboBlJ6F5j4afCaL8VCHgPX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Wider resetless ifetch replay cache\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest winning change showed that the safest remaining cycle gain is not\n+  branch prediction, but replaying immutable hot-loop instructions when the\n+  random instruction bus stalls. The current replay table is only 8 entries and\n+  direct-mapped, so CoreMark loop bodies can still conflict on pc[4:2] and fall\n+  back to bubbles even after the instruction was previously fetched.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that added queues, store buffers, bypass paths, or\n+  predictor metadata regressed because they lengthened common control paths.\n+  A larger direct-mapped replay cache keeps the same no-repair frontend shape\n+  while improving the hit rate of the one mechanism that has already produced a\n+  large fitness win.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rebuild the IF replay table as a 16-entry direct-mapped, valid-gated replay\n+  cache indexed by pc[5:2]. Fill it only on accepted io_imemReady fetches, and\n+  on io_imemReady=0 hits keep supplying the cached instruction through the\n+  existing imem_effective_ready path. Do not add branch prediction metadata,\n+  target repair state, or any EX feedback.\n+\n+  Make the replay tag and instruction payload arrays resetless and reset only\n+  the valid bits, since invalid entries are never consumed. This offsets some of\n+  the extra storage cost and should let synthesis map the cache as small\n+  distributed storage instead of a reset-heavy flop bundle. The expected result\n+  is fewer random iStall bubbles in hot CoreMark loops with a smaller Fmax risk\n+  than any predictor or FIFO-style frontend decoupling.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expand the replay table to 16 direct-mapped entries, index by pc[5:2], and reset only valid bits while leaving tag/instruction payload storage resetless.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r11s1\n+title: \"Wider resetless ifetch replay cache\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest winning change showed that the safest remaining cycle gain is not\n+  branch prediction, but replaying immutable hot-loop instructions when the\n+  random instruction bus stalls. The current replay table is only 8 entries and\n+  direct-mapped, so CoreMark loop bodies can still conflict on pc[4:2] and fall\n+  back to bubbles even after the instruction was previously fetched.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts that added queues, store buffers, bypass paths, or\n+  predictor metadata regressed because they lengthened common control paths.\n+  A larger direct-mapped replay cache keeps the same no-repair frontend shape\n+  while improving the hit rate of the one mechanism that has already produced a\n+  large fitness win.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Rebuild the IF replay table as a 16-entry direct-mapped, valid-gated replay\n+  cache indexed by pc[5:2]. Fill it only on accep