{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612764780,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f754dffezkQZ4gdYkTnXqa","part":{"id":"prt_e1d94fad7001NVtYi5eCnw2Tbx","messageID":"msg_e1d94f403001NBmTQbHT896wnq","sessionID":"ses_1e26f754dffezkQZ4gdYkTnXqa","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis YAML now under `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/` with short-form RTL paths.","time":{"start":1778612763351,"end":1778612764779},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a074a36020d930a016a037a1b415881909ad20d96ee4e414a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612786819,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f754dffezkQZ4gdYkTnXqa","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_RqjtOsBDiGG4egT2BaEtce5s","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Warm replay during backend stalls\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current 8-entry IF replay table produced the largest recent improvement by\n+  converting random instruction-bus stalls into useful hot-loop instructions.\n+  Follow-up attempts to widen or reset-retime the table regressed, which points\n+  away from adding capacity on the fetch critical path and toward improving how\n+  often the existing table is populated.\n+\n+  Backend stalls from dmem backpressure, load-use bubbles, and iterative divide\n+  already stop decode from consuming the current fetch slot. Those cycles can be\n+  used to issue harmless sequential instruction fetches and train the replay\n+  table, because instruction memory is immutable and wrong-path replay fills do\n+  not affect architectural state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an opportunistic replay warmer inside IF. When the architectural PC is\n+  held for a non-redirect backend stall and the instruction bus is ready, drive\n+  io_imemAddr from a small sequential prefetch cursor instead of the held PC and\n+  fill the existing replay table with the returned instruction. Keep out.pc,\n+  RVFI-visible instruction flow, redirect handling, and decode consumption tied\n+  to the architectural PC; the warmer only trains replay entries while ID/EX is\n+  already held or bubbled.\n+\n+  This should improve CoreMark cycles by turning otherwise idle backend-stall\n+  cycles into future ifetch replay hits, without adding a skid queue, branch\n+  predictor, target repair metadata, or a wider replay lookup. Constrain the\n+  cursor to sequential in-bounds RAM instruction addresses and flush/restart it\n+  on redirects so invariant 6 and precise NRET=1 retirement remain intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a backend-stall-only sequential replay warmer that uses idle ready ifetch cycles to fill the existing replay table without advancing the architectural PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, pass a prefetch-eligible stall indication into IF while preserving the current NRET=1 RVFI and bus port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, expose backend-stall versus imem-stall intent so IF warms replay only when decode is already held for non-fetch reasons.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r12s1\n+title: \"Warm replay during backend stalls\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current 8-entry IF replay table produced the largest recent improvement by\n+  converting random instruction-bus stalls into useful hot-loop instructions.\n+  Follow-up attempts to widen or reset-retime the table regressed, which points\n+  away from adding capacity on the fetch critical path and toward improving how\n+  often the existing table is populated.\n+\n+  Backend stalls from dmem backpressure, load-use bubbles, and iterative divide\n+  already stop decode from consuming the current fetch slot. Those cycles can be\n+  used to issue harmless sequential instruction fetches and train the replay\n+  table, because instruction memory is immutable and wrong-path replay fills do\n+  not affect architectural state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an opportunistic replay warmer inside IF. When the architectural PC is\n+  held for a non-redirect backend stall and the instruction bus is ready, drive\n+  io_imemAddr from a small sequential prefetch cursor instead of the held PC and\n+  fill the existing replay table with the returned instruction. Keep out.pc,\n+  RVFI-visible instruction flow, redirect handling, and decode consumption tied\n+  to the architectural PC; the warmer only trains replay entries while ID/EX is\n+  already held or bubbled.\n+\n+  This should improve CoreMark cycles by turning otherwise idle backend-stall\n+  cycles into future ifetch replay hits, without adding a skid queue, branch\n+  predictor, target repair metadata, or a wider replay lookup. Constrain the\n+  cursor to sequential in-bounds RAM instruction addresses and flush/restart it\n+  on redirects so invariant 6 and precise NRET=1 retirement remain intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a backend-stall-only sequential replay warmer that uses idle ready ifetch cycles to fill the existing replay table without advancing the architectural PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, pass a prefetch-eligible stall indication into IF while preserving the current NRET=1 RVFI and bus port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"If needed, expose backend-stall versus imem-stall intent so IF warms replay only when decode is already held for non-fetch reasons.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/