KeTd5e0wh\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I’ll write the hypothesis as a dedicated EX fast-add/AGU split: it avoids replay and predictor paths, and targets the common ADD/load-store address path currently sharing the full ALU/multiplier result mux.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778616632661,\"end\":1778616632828},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_05002c5d921bfa43016a03893887488199a4136f522d4448c4\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n18: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616633276,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_x44EQlDGdaaEIpkPPQBwVEVu\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":200},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses</path>\\n<type>directory</type>\\n<entries>\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r10s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r11s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r12s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r13s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r14s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r1s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r3s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r4s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r5s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r6s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r7s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r8s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-001-r9s0.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r10s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r11s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r12s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r13s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r14s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r6s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r7s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r8s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r3s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r4s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.log\\n.agent.hyp-2026051... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n19: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778616633386,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dd00829001DkE8RAsUYHLy2W\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dcf6160001ZPh6H7RVvB3j8z\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":61381,\"input\":2317,\"output\":121,\"reasoning\":2111,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":56832}},\"cost\":0}}\n20: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778616634755,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dd00d820016Gnviazg0RfSc8\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dd0084f0011WVGdcMrMCq0y4\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n21: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616720817,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_nD5DrCSIOlxBK1QJJrK6DBwN\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":200},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\\n2: title: \\\"Victim-slot ifetch replay predictor\\\"\\n3: category: predictor\\n4: motivation: |\\n5:   Branch-target predictors, RAS variants, countdown loop predictors, and\\n6:   replay-table capacity/hash changes have mostly regressed because extra PC\\n7:   muxing, EX repair metadata, or wider fetch routing cost more Fmax than they\\n8:   recovered in CoreMark cycles. The one predictor that improved this core is\\n9:   the accepted-fetch instruction replay table, which hides random hot-loop\\n10:   instruction stalls without predicting control flow.\\n11: \\n12:   The remaining plausible replay weakness is direct-mapped thrashing between a\\n13:   small number of hot PCs that share pc[4:2]. A single victim slot targets that\\n14:   specific failure mode without widening the primary table or changing the\\n15:   normal pc+4 fetch path.\\n16: hypothesis: |\\n17:   Keep the current 8-entry accepted-fetch replay predictor as the primary\\n18:   lookup, but add one fully-tagged victim replay slot. When an accepted fetch\\n19:   replaces a valid primary entry with a different tag, move the evicted tag and\\n20:   instruction into the victim slot. On io_imemReady=0, first check the indexed\\n21:   primary entry; if it misses, check the victim slot and replay its instruction\\n22:   on a tag hit. Do not predict branches or jumps, do not add predicted-next-PC\\n23:   metadata, and do not... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(End of file - total 21 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778616516181,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce3e53001enjvu2TXJA1iuS\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce39a0001T76f4O65hpLin0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778616530638,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce702b001xQMreI906F3om1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce39a0001T76f4O65hpLin0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I’ll ground the proposal in the recorded outcomes first, focusing on prior structural attempts so the YAML does not rediscover a known regression.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778616528939,\"end\":1778616530635},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_05c797344cc2adcf016a0388d0d254819b9dabc0bea663037b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616530707,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_oLSGzx9UMQuafsQQDlT5pjOm\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/LESSONS.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-001-r1s0 (improvement, +41.63%): Moving DIV/REM out of the combinational ALU mux into an iterative ex_stage div_unit removes rare divide hardware from the FPGA critical path while CoreMark's divide-sparse mix hides the stall latency.\\n2: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-002-r1s1 (broken, n/a): Multi-cycle M-units need a done/ack guard that prevents a held ID/EX M instruction from reasserting start on the ready cycle, or RV32M retirement can lose/corrupt the result in cosim.\\n3: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-003-r1s2 (regression, +5.13%): IF-stage static branch/JAL predecode can lengthen the imem_data-to-next_pc fetch critical path enough that Fmax loss outweighs CoreMark loop-back bubble savings.\\n4: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-001-r2s0 (regression, -4.44%): Sharing MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU through one sign-controlled 33x33 product can hurt Fmax because operand-signedness muxing and the wider 66-bit multiply cone outweigh removing parallel 32x32 product nets.\\n5: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-002-r2s1 (regression, -21.07%): A two-entry IF skid queue can cost more than it hides in this shallow CoreMark pipeline, as fetch_pc/valid/pop/full muxing outweighed limited overlap between random imem stalls and backend stalls.\\n6: - 2026-05-12 hyp-20260512-003-r2s2 (regression, -43.44%): A PC-indexed BTB still puts tag/counter/target lookup plus predicted-next-PC plumbing on the fetch/control path, and in this shallow CoreMark pipeline that cost can swamp warmed-up loo... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616530731,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_bPpg1bJzDBcHSIIcmk36dmQN\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/core.yaml\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":120},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/core.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: name: bench\\n2: description: Frozen LLM-benchmark fixture core. Identical RTL to baseline at the bench-fixture-v1\\n3:   freeze point. The benchmark matrix clones from the bench-fixture-v1 orphan branch\\n4:   and operates only on this directory.\\n5: isa: rv32im\\n6: nret: 1\\n7: target_fpga: tang-nano-20k\\n8: targets:\\n9:   fmax_mhz: 135\\n10:   lut4: 10000\\n11:   coremark_iter_s: 300\\n12:   coremark_per_mhz: 2.2\\n13: current:\\n14:   fmax_mhz: 220.22\\n15:   lut4: 5453\\n16:   ff: 2138\\n17:   coremark_iter_s: 2.0e-06\\n18:   coremark_per_mhz: 0.0\\n19:   source_id: hyp-20260512-003-r10s2\\n20:   updated: '2026-05-12T18:46:17.767342Z'\\n\\n(End of file - total 20 lines)\\n</content>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"name: bench\\ndescription: Frozen LLM-benchmark fixture core. Identical RTL to baseline at the bench-fixture-v1\\n  freeze point. The benchmark matrix clones from the bench-fixture-v1 orphan branch\\n  and operates only on this directory.\\nisa: rv32im\\nnret: 1\\ntarget_fpga: tang-nano-20k\\ntargets:\\n  fmax_mhz: 135\\n  lut4: 10000\\n  coremark_iter_s: 300\\n  coremark_per_mhz: 2.2\\ncurrent:\\n  fmax_mhz: 220.22\\n  lut4: 5453\\n  ff: 2138\\n  coremark_iter_s: 2.0e-06\\n  coremark_per_mhz: 0.0\\n  source_id: hyp-20260512-003-r10s2\\n  updated: '2026-05-12T18:46:17.767342Z'\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[]},\"title\":\"cores/bench/core.yaml\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778616530726,\"end\":1778616530731}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_05c797344cc2adcf016a0388d27c50819ba7d8669dae8e8b07\"}},\"id\":\"prt_e1dce7725... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616530742,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_D11PouURAaZ0Wlrlg2GPyKo1\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"category.*structural|structural\",\"path\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments\",\"include\":\"log.jsonl\"},\"output\":\"Found 14 matches\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\\n  Line 3: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Decouple RV32M from EX critical path\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"structural\\\", \\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current EX stage contains the full RV32IM ALU, including three 64-bit multiply products and combinational divide/remainder logic. Even when CoreMark is executing ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, and memory instructions, that wide M-extension datapath remains part of the synthesized execute-stage cone and likely limits Fmax near the Tang Nano 20K LUT budget.\\\\n\\\\nA structural split that keeps common RV32I operations single-cycle while moving RV32M work into a dedicated busy/ready unit should raise Fmax and reduce routing pressure. CoreMark uses multiply but rarely needs divide in the timed loop, so a modest multiply latency penalty should be outweighed by a shorter critical path.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": {\\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current EX stage contains the full RV32IM ALU, including three 64-bit multiply products and combinational divide/remainder logic. Even when CoreMark is executing ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, and memory instructions, that wide M-extension datapath remains part of the synthesized execute-stage cone and likely limits Fmax near the Tang Nano 20K LUT budget.\\\\n\\\\nA structural split that keeps common RV32I operations single-cycle while moving RV32M work into a dedicated busy/ready unit should raise Fmax and reduce routing pressure. CoreMark uses multiply but rarely needs divide in the ti... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778616530774,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce7755001sU0gvGn852B7T3\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce39a0001T76f4O65hpLin0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":42359,\"input\":26238,\"output\":245,\"reasoning\":516,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":15360}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778616531833,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce7b7700159P9H5Wm2HcLjA\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce7772001Nx8kNutUMB0UAd\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778616582705,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dcf4168001WFDuvKFUJGvMI4\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce7772001Nx8kNutUMB0UAd\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The structural history strongly penalizes added fetch/control machinery; the safer open direction is a local structural change off the common RV32I path, where it can improve CPI without touching replay, redirect, or forwarding timing.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778616582504,\"end\":1778616582704},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_03432ebcbe960be2016a038906609c8199bb301bdc4d97d3b6\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616584240,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_SHEpDwVrFDl4AMk6GjhpvRjv\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"ALU_DIV|div_unit|count_q|div_by_zero|signed_overflow\",\"path\":\"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/rtl\",\"include\":\"*.sv\"},\"output\":\"Found 30 matches\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/rtl/ex_stage.sv:\\n  Line 83:   logic        div_unit_busy;\\n\\n  Line 93:       ALU_DIV, ALU_DIVU, ALU_REM, ALU_REMU:\\n\\n  Line 100:   assign div_signed = (in.ctrl.alu_op == ALU_DIV) || (in.ctrl.alu_op == ALU_REM);\\n\\n  Line 102:   assign div_start  = div_op && !div_unit_busy && !div_done && !stall;\\n\\n  Line 108:   div_unit u_div (\\n\\n  Line 117:     .busy      (div_unit_busy),\\n\\n  Line 221:         // The divide instruction stays in ID/EX while div_unit runs. Keep\\n\\n\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/rtl/core_pkg.sv:\\n  Line 36:   localparam logic [4:0] ALU_DIV    = 5'd15;\\n\\n  Line 37:   localparam logic [4:0] ALU_DIVU   = 5'd16;\\n\\n\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/rtl/decoder.sv:\\n  Line 91:             10'b0000001_100: alu_op = ALU_DIV;\\n\\n  Line 92:             10'b0000001_101: alu_op = ALU_DIVU;\\n\\n\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-