\":\"Found 43 matches\\n/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl:\\n  Line 1: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"baseline-bench-4c67411\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Baseline retest for cores/bench\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"outcome\\\": \\\"improvement\\\", \\\"fitness\\\": 282.82, \\\"delta_pct\\\": 0.0, \\\"vs_baseline\\\": 0.0, \\\"fmax_mhz\\\": 127.03, \\\"ipc_coremark\\\": 2e-06, \\\"cycles\\\": 4491485, \\\"iterations\\\": 10, \\\"lut4\\\": 9563, \\\"ff\\\": 1866, \\\"seeds\\\": [128.72, 127.03, 123.02], \\\"formal_passed\\\": true, \\\"cosim_passed\\\": true, \\\"error\\\": null, \\\"implementation_notes\\\": \\\"\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"2026-05-12T14:04:33.574191Z\\\", \\\"round_id\\\": 0, \\\"slot\\\": 0}\\n\\n  Line 2: {\\\"id\\\": \\\"hyp-20260512-001-r1s0\\\", \\\"title\\\": \\\"Iterative divider off ALU critical path\\\", \\\"category\\\": \\\"micro_opt\\\", \\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current ALU implements RV32IM DIV/REM with combinational / and % operators\\\\nin the same execute-stage result mux as the common integer and multiply ops.\\\\nCoreMark is dominated by adds, branches, loads, stores, and multiplies; rare\\\\ndivision hardware can still cap FPGA Fmax and consume LUTs even when it is not\\\\non the dynamic hot path.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": {\\\"motivation\\\": \\\"The current ALU implements RV32IM DIV/REM with combinational / and % operators\\\\nin the same execute-stage result mux as the common integer and multiply ops.\\\\nCoreMark is dominated by adds, branches, loads, stores, and multiplies; rare\\\\ndivision hardware can still cap FPGA Fmax and consume LUTs even when it is not\\\\non the dynamic hot path.\\\\n\\\", \\\"hypothesis\\\": \\\"Replace only DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU with a small iterative divider/rem unit and\\\\... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n5: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778616527126,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce6915001bCNHDlt90Saiay\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce3a17001ZT9KieArBYZncw\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":42049,\"input\":4223,\"output\":159,\"reasoning\":291,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":37376}},\"cost\":0}}\n6: {\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1778616528061,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dce6cbc001rzp1aqRW10v65T\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce6937001FP1vfe27Lo4Eh0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n7: {\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1778616632683,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dd003fc001zdqCuOQhb4cmXV\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce6937001FP1vfe27Lo4Eh0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The most defensible `micro_opt` angle is another control-pruning pass: keep the current replay and pipeline structure intact, but stop carrying simple funct3-derived control bits through stage registers when the instruction word is already carried for RVFI.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1778616632316,\"end\":1778616632681},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0ac1bc42007c6d31016a0389382d34819ba5fd68edce7188a5\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n8: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1778616644423,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"apply_patch\",\"callID\":\"call_jregjB48eC3xsLcyhh8JGAjs\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"patchText\":\"*** Begin Patch\\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r15s0.yaml\\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r15s0\\n+title: \\\"Derive funct3 controls locally\\\"\\n+category: micro_opt\\n+motivation: |\\n+  The best prior micro-opt wins came from removing cold datapath logic and pruning\\n+  pipeline control state, while recent replay and predictor follow-ups regressed\\n+  when they added fetch-path muxing or metadata. The current core still carries\\n+  several control bits that are direct copies of instruction funct3 fields even\\n+  though the full instruction word already travels through the pipeline for RVFI.\\n+  Those redundant bits do not improve CPI, but they add decode outputs, stage\\n+  flops, and routing pressure in a design that appears fanout-limited on FPGA.\\n+hypothesis: |\\n+  Remove redundant funct3-derived control payload from the pipeline. Derive the\\n+  branch comparison op in EX from the ID/EX instruction bits, derive load/store\\n+  width and load signedness in MEM from the EX/MEM instruction bits, and derive\\n+  the MEM/WB load-result select from mem_read rather than carrying mem_to_reg\\n+  through ID/EX and EX/MEM. The decoder should still validate every opcode and\\n+  funct field exactly as today, with is_illegal defaulting high, but it no longer\\n+  needs to export these simple mirror controls.\\n+\\n+  This keeps the five-stage timing, accepted-fetch replay table, NRET=1 RVFI\\n+  contract, trap semantics, memory alignment behavior, and CoreMark instruction\\n+  count unchanged. If the current implementation is still limited by decode and\\n+  pipeline-control routing, trimming these bits should modestly improve median\\n+  Fmax without risking the cycle-count regressions seen from predictor, replay,\\n+  multiplier, and bypass... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n9: {\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1778616644477,\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_e1dd0337c001HfxZrvFxBajrbX\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_e1dce6937001FP1vfe27Lo4Eh0\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_1e231c63affeCxs3BPM8Ye0FON\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":70820,\"input\":22932,\"output\":756,\"reasoning\":5660,\"ca