{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778616722686,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh","part":{"id":"prt_e1dd164fd001mBx4dyAjIZBBvk","messageID":"msg_e1dd15e04001JLS6GKyygivKGQ","sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh","snapshot":"7dee8224c7638b7d863de1978a420a6ea61437d6","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778616774263,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh","part":{"id":"prt_e1dd22c7f001AOVuCx9RJifDAV","messageID":"msg_e1dd15e04001JLS6GKyygivKGQ","sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh","type":"text","text":"I’m adjusting the proposal to a stronger structural target: a corrected operand-aware load interlock. The earlier false-stall idea broke on RVFI source reporting, so this version explicitly separates execution operands from RVFI raw source capture instead of dropping the raw fields.","time":{"start":1778616773759,"end":1778616774261},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_097a715835c3601f016a0389c5901c819686967dd872386369","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616787486,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0wh","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_7SwdAclWdal5IAIakBvlhfPC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Operand-aware load interlock\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls after every load when the load destination\n+  matches either raw register field of the following instruction. That is\n+  conservative for RVFI, but it also creates false bubbles for immediates,\n+  jumps, upper-immediate ops, fences, and traps whose bit fields alias the\n+  load rd without being execution operands. CoreMark has many load-adjacent\n+  pointer and immediate operations, so recovering even a small fraction of\n+  these bubbles can improve iterations per cycle.\n+\n+  A prior false-load-use attempt broke because unused raw rs1/rs2 fields still\n+  need correct RVFI register data. The structural opportunity remains if the\n+  core separates execution operand readiness from RVFI source reporting instead\n+  of treating every raw field as a data dependency.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add explicit source-use metadata for the instruction entering ID/EX and use\n+  it only for the load-use interlock. Branches, stores, JALR, and R-type ops\n+  still stall when they consume a load result, but I-type immediates, LUI,\n+  AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, EBREAK, and illegal instructions no longer stall solely\n+  because an unused raw field aliases the older load rd.\n+\n+  Preserve RVFI correctness by keeping the raw rs1/rs2 addresses and adding a\n+  small RVFI-source repair path for unused aliased fields. Existing MEM/WB\n+  forwarding covers older writes; the one-cycle load-ahead case should take the\n+  MEM-stage sign/zero-extended load value into the EX/MEM RVFI rs value field\n+  without feeding the ALU operand mux. This keeps the actual execute operands\n+  and redirect path conservative while allowing false interlocks to disappear.\n+\n+  This is a structural split between operand consumption and retirement\n+  reporting, not a predictor or fetch replay change. It keeps NRET=1, raw RVFI\n+  source reporting, trap discipline, and memory ordering intact while targeting\n+  CPI instead of adding more fetch-path timing risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1_used/rs2_used execution-use metadata to the ID/EX control payload, while keeping raw rs1/rs2 addresses for RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive execution source-use bits from the decoded opcode class without changing the decoder's illegal-by-default validation semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate the load-use interlock with rs1_used/rs2_used so unused raw fields no longer create false load bubbles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Separate ALU operand forwarding from RVFI source-value capture and repair unused aliased RVFI source values from load-data forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage extended load result as a sideband RVFI repair source without changing dmem request behavior or writeback data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the source-use metadata and MEM load repair sideband between ID, hazard, MEM, and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level port shape.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,50 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Operand-aware load interlock\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls after every load when the load destination\n+  matches either raw register field of the following instruction. That is\n+  conservative for RVFI, but it also creates false bubbles for immediates,\n+  jumps, upper-immediate ops, fences, and traps whose bit fields alias the\n+  load rd without being execution operands. CoreMark has many load-adjacent\n+  pointer and immediate operations, so recovering even a small fraction of\n+  these bubbles can improve iterations per cycle.\n+\n+  A prior false-load-use attempt broke because unused raw rs1/rs2 fields still\n+  need correct RVFI register data. The structural opportunity remains if the\n+  core separates execution operand readiness from RVFI source reporting instead\n+  of treating every raw field as a data dependency.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add explicit source-use metadata for the instruction entering ID/EX and use\n+  it only for the load-use interlock. Branches, stores, JALR, and R-type ops\n+  still stall when they consume a load result, but I-type immediates, LUI,\n+  AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, EBREAK, and illegal instructions no longer stall solely\n+  because an unused raw field aliases the older load rd.\n+\n+  Preserve RVFI correctness by keeping the raw rs1/rs2 addresses and adding a\n+  small RVFI-source repair path for unused aliased fields. Existing MEM/WB\n+  forwarding covers older writes; the one-cycle load-ahead case should take the\n+  MEM-stage sign/zero-extended load value into the EX/MEM RVFI rs value field\n+  without feeding the ALU operand mux. This keeps the actual execute operands\n+  and redirect path conservative while allowing false interlocks to disappear.\n+\n+  This is a structural split between operand consumption and retirement\n+  reporting, not a predictor or fetch replay change. It keeps NRET=1, raw RVFI\n+  source reporting, trap discipline, and memory ordering intact while targeting\n+  CPI instead of adding more fetch-path timing risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1_used/rs2_used execution-use metadata to the ID/EX control payload, while keeping raw rs1/rs2 addresses for RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive execution source-use bits from the decoded opcode class without changing the decoder's illegal-by-default validation semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate the load-use interlock with rs1_used/rs2_used so unused raw fields no longer create false load bubbles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Separate ALU operand forwarding from RVFI source-value capture and repair unused aliased RVFI source values from load-data forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage extended load result as a sideband RVFI repair source without changing dmem request behavior or writeback data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the source-use metadata and MEM load repair sideband between ID, hazard, MEM, and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level port shape.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,50 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r15s1\n+title: \"Operand-aware load interlock\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current hazard unit stalls after every load when the load destination\n+  matches either raw register field of the following instruction. That is\n+  conservative for RVFI, but it also creates false bubbles for immediates,\n+  jumps, upper-immediate ops, fences, and traps whose bit fields alias the\n+  load rd without being execution operands. CoreMark has many load-adjacent\n+  pointer and immediate operations, so recovering even a small fraction of\n+  these bubbles can improve iterations per cycle.\n+\n+  A prior false-load-use attempt broke because unused raw rs1/rs2 fields still\n+  need correct RVFI register data. The structural opportunity remains if the\n+  core separates execution operand readiness from RVFI source reporting instead\n+  of treating every raw field as a data dependency.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add explicit source-use metadata for the instruction entering ID/EX and use\n+  it only for the load-use interlock. Branches, stores, JALR, and R-type ops\n+  still stall when they consume a load result, but I-type immediates, LUI,\n+  AUIPC, JAL, FENCE, EBREAK, and illegal instructions no longer stall solely\n+  because an unused raw field aliases the older load rd.\n+\n+  Preserve RVFI correctness by keeping the raw rs1/rs2 addresses and adding a\n+  small RVFI-source repair path for unused aliased fields. Existing MEM/WB\n+  forwarding covers older writes; the one-cycle load-ahead case should take the\n+  MEM-stage sign/zero-extended load value into the EX/MEM RVFI rs value field\n+  without feeding the ALU operand mux. This keeps the actual execute operands\n+  and redirect path conservative while allowing false interlocks to disappear.\n+\n+  This is a structural split between operand consumption and retirement\n+  reporting, not a predictor or fetch replay change. It keeps NRET=1, raw RVFI\n+  source reporting, trap discipline, and memory ordering intact while targeting\n+  CPI instead of adding more fetch-path timing risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact rs1_used/rs2_used execution-use metadata to the ID/EX control payload, while keeping raw rs1/rs2 addresses for RVFI.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive execution source-use bits from the decoded opcode class without changing the decoder's illegal-by-default validation semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Gate the load-use interlock with rs1_used/rs2_used so unused raw fields no longer create false load bubbles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Separate ALU operand forwarding from RVFI source-value capture and repair unused aliased RVFI source values from load-data forwarding.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose the MEM-stage extended load result as a sideband RVFI repair source without changing dmem request behavior or writeback data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the source-use metadata and MEM load repair sideband between ID, hazard, MEM, and EX while preserving the NRET=1 top-level port shape.\"\n","additions":50,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r15s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778616787482,"end":1778616787485}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_097a715835c3601f016a0389c61c008196aa7423a01d12468d"}},"id":"prt_e1dd22e77001Cmjb89sR8OVe2l","sessionID":"ses_1e231c6a5ffeimPTYKeTd5e0