{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594804854,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea765ffemioNX02efoosD5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cmESx3dw8ZoulaB5xK6Ldiam","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple RV32M from EX critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage contains the full RV32IM ALU, including three 64-bit multiply products and combinational divide/remainder logic. Even when CoreMark is executing ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, and memory instructions, that wide M-extension datapath remains part of the synthesized execute-stage cone and likely limits Fmax near the Tang Nano 20K LUT budget.\n+\n+  A structural split that keeps common RV32I operations single-cycle while moving RV32M work into a dedicated busy/ready unit should raise Fmax and reduce routing pressure. CoreMark uses multiply but rarely needs divide in the timed loop, so a modest multiply latency penalty should be outweighed by a shorter critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a separate M-unit and make EX a one-cycle stage for RV32I plus a multi-cycle/busy stage only for ALU_MUL*, ALU_DIV*, and ALU_REM*. Implement multiply as a short pipelined DSP-friendly path and division/remainder as an iterative unit, with the hazard unit freezing IF/ID/EX while an M operation is outstanding and releasing exactly one EX/MEM result when ready.\n+\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the M-unit's substituted algebraic results one-cycle or equivalently ready immediately so the existing fast formal gate remains tractable. RVFI still retires through the existing MEM/WB boundary, preserving nret=1 ordering and trap semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated RV32M execute unit with pipelined multiply, iterative divide/remainder, ready/valid handshaking, and ALTOPS-compatible formal behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the common combinational ALU path, leaving RV32I operations and ALTOPS-compatible hooks for M-unit integration.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route M-extension operations through the new M-unit, hold the EX/MEM register while the result is pending, and emit a single completed result into the normal retirement path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-busy stall input so IF, ID, and EX preserve precise in-order state during multi-cycle M operations without creating duplicate retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX busy/ready control into the top-level stall network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple RV32M from EX critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage contains the full RV32IM ALU, including three 64-bit multiply products and combinational divide/remainder logic. Even when CoreMark is executing ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, and memory instructions, that wide M-extension datapath remains part of the synthesized execute-stage cone and likely limits Fmax near the Tang Nano 20K LUT budget.\n+\n+  A structural split that keeps common RV32I operations single-cycle while moving RV32M work into a dedicated busy/ready unit should raise Fmax and reduce routing pressure. CoreMark uses multiply but rarely needs divide in the timed loop, so a modest multiply latency penalty should be outweighed by a shorter critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a separate M-unit and make EX a one-cycle stage for RV32I plus a multi-cycle/busy stage only for ALU_MUL*, ALU_DIV*, and ALU_REM*. Implement multiply as a short pipelined DSP-friendly path and division/remainder as an iterative unit, with the hazard unit freezing IF/ID/EX while an M operation is outstanding and releasing exactly one EX/MEM result when ready.\n+\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the M-unit's substituted algebraic results one-cycle or equivalently ready immediately so the existing fast formal gate remains tractable. RVFI still retires through the existing MEM/WB boundary, preserving nret=1 ordering and trap semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated RV32M execute unit with pipelined multiply, iterative divide/remainder, ready/valid handshaking, and ALTOPS-compatible formal behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the common combinational ALU path, leaving RV32I operations and ALTOPS-compatible hooks for M-unit integration.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route M-extension operations through the new M-unit, hold the EX/MEM register while the result is pending, and emit a single completed result into the normal retirement path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-busy stall input so IF, ID, and EX preserve precise in-order state during multi-cycle M operations without creating duplicate retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX busy/ready control into the top-level stall network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,25 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r1s1\n+title: \"Decouple RV32M from EX critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current EX stage contains the full RV32IM ALU, including three 64-bit multiply products and combinational divide/remainder logic. Even when CoreMark is executing ordinary RV32I ALU, branch, and memory instructions, that wide M-extension datapath remains part of the synthesized execute-stage cone and likely limits Fmax near the Tang Nano 20K LUT budget.\n+\n+  A structural split that keeps common RV32I operations single-cycle while moving RV32M work into a dedicated busy/ready unit should raise Fmax and reduce routing pressure. CoreMark uses multiply but rarely needs divide in the timed loop, so a modest multiply latency penalty should be outweighed by a shorter critical path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a separate M-unit and make EX a one-cycle stage for RV32I plus a multi-cycle/busy stage only for ALU_MUL*, ALU_DIV*, and ALU_REM*. Implement multiply as a short pipelined DSP-friendly path and division/remainder as an iterative unit, with the hazard unit freezing IF/ID/EX while an M operation is outstanding and releasing exactly one EX/MEM result when ready.\n+\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the M-unit's substituted algebraic results one-cycle or equivalently ready immediately so the existing fast formal gate remains tractable. RVFI still retires through the existing MEM/WB boundary, preserving nret=1 ordering and trap semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/m_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated RV32M execute unit with pipelined multiply, iterative divide/remainder, ready/valid handshaking, and ALTOPS-compatible formal behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real multiply/divide/remainder operators from the common combinational ALU path, leaving RV32I operations and ALTOPS-compatible hooks for M-unit integration.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route M-extension operations through the new M-unit, hold the EX/MEM register while the result is pending, and emit a single completed result into the normal retirement path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an execute-busy stall input so IF, ID, and EX preserve precise in-order state during multi-cycle M operations without creating duplicate retirements.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the EX busy/ready control into the top-level stall network while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n","additions":25,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r1s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778594804845,"end":1778594804852}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03c119cf7e48b457016a0333dc6ec08197a5c552816fcbf034"}},"id":"prt_e1c82955e001VJZ5CZXC3n0JY5","sessionID":"ses_1e37ea765ffemioNX02efoosD5","messageID":"msg_e1c828214001DbiCOtSUD8lthB"}}
