{"type":"text","timestamp":1778596686131,"sessionID":"ses_1e36402c1ffeWw0UF74O8zUKWR","part":{"id":"prt_e1c9fa740002w4nkxu6QL01Y73","messageID":"msg_e1c9f81b0001ufTEB3YdRtNNFb","sessionID":"ses_1e36402c1ffeWw0UF74O8zUKWR","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis now as a new YAML file under `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/`, keeping the proposed edits scoped to `cores/bench` RTL/test paths only.","time":{"start":1778596685632,"end":1778596686130},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d54943162870398016a033b4d85288195b9ec2a4ef15e0230","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596707180,"sessionID":"ses_1e36402c1ffeWw0UF74O8zUKWR","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Prxl7J59VhAKXsctjjcK6d0A","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Decouple fetch with skid queue\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current frontend treats every low io_imemReady cycle as an immediate\n+  decode bubble, and backend stalls hold the PC so the core cannot fetch ahead\n+  while memory, load-use, or iterative divide latency is already stopping\n+  retirement. In the tournament cosim mode both instruction and data buses see\n+  random stalls, so overlapping independent frontend availability with backend\n+  stalls can improve CoreMark cycles without relying on the failed IF-stage\n+  instruction predecode path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a small two-entry instruction skid/prefetch queue between the fetch PC\n+  and ID. The fetch side advances and enqueues whenever io_imemReady is high and\n+  the queue is not full; the decode side consumes only when the existing backend\n+  hazard logic allows ID to advance. Redirects flush the queue and restart fetch\n+  at the resolved target, preserving precise RVFI retirement and the NRET=1 port\n+  contract.\n+\n+  This structural decoupling should hide a fraction of random iStall cycles\n+  behind dmem stalls, load-use bubbles, and divide busy cycles, while adding only\n+  a shallow FIFO and PC muxes instead of putting branch predecode on the\n+  imem_data-to-next_pc critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the single PC-to-ID combinational fetch path with a two-entry instruction queue, fetch PC, decode pop, redirect flush, and empty/full handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Stop treating raw io_imemReady as a backend stall source; let IF emit invalid bubbles when the queue is empty while backend hazards still gate decode consumption.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/hazard handshake so backend stalls prevent queue pops but do not prevent independent instruction prefetch when queue space is available.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add only the minimal fetch-queue metadata or valid/ready bundle fields needed for the decoupled IF-to-ID interface, preserving the existing RVFI payload semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Decouple fetch with skid queue\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current frontend treats every low io_imemReady cycle as an immediate\n+  decode bubble, and backend stalls hold the PC so the core cannot fetch ahead\n+  while memory, load-use, or iterative divide latency is already stopping\n+  retirement. In the tournament cosim mode both instruction and data buses see\n+  random stalls, so overlapping independent frontend availability with backend\n+  stalls can improve CoreMark cycles without relying on the failed IF-stage\n+  instruction predecode path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Insert a small two-entry instruction skid/prefetch queue between the fetch PC\n+  and ID. The fetch side advances and enqueues whenever io_imemReady is high and\n+  the queue is not full; the decode side consumes only when the existing backend\n+  hazard logic allows ID to advance. Redirects flush the queue and restart fetch\n+  at the resolved target, preserving precise RVFI retirement and the NRET=1 port\n+  contract.\n+\n+  This structural decoupling should hide a fraction of random iStall cycles\n+  behind dmem stalls, load-use bubbles, and divide busy cycles, while adding only\n+  a shallow FIFO and PC muxes instead of putting branch predecode on the\n+  imem_data-to-next_pc critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the single PC-to-ID combinational fetch path with a two-entry instruction queue, fetch PC, decode pop, redirect flush, and empty/full handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Stop treating raw io_imemReady as a backend stall source; let IF emit invalid bubbles when the queue is empty while backend hazards still gate decode consumption.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/hazard handshake so backend stalls prevent queue pops but do not prevent independent instruction prefetch when queue space is available.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add only the minimal fetch-queue metadata or valid/ready bundle fields needed for the decoupled IF-to-ID interface, preserving the existing RVFI payload semantics.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n=====================================================