{"type":"text","timestamp":1778598709287,"sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","part":{"id":"prt_e1cbe7f39001z7ihYWws8BFVIq","messageID":"msg_e1cbbbcaa0014R2KBkohSbsC7r","sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","type":"text","text":"Prior structural attempts focused on broad M-unit decoupling and fetch buffering; both either broke or regressed. I’m writing a narrower structural hypothesis around a normal-RAM store buffer, which targets random dmem stalls without adding fetch-path predictor logic or changing the NRET=1 contract.","time":{"start":1778598707001,"end":1778598709285},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_067c6419602d4864016a034332daac8194bcdffa60a923a2fb","phase":"commentary"}}}}
