{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598738541,"sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_drYEdpeIezv8kH6Vfi699HDh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"One-entry RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current in-order pipeline freezes behind every STORE whenever io_dmemReady\n+  is low, even though most stores do not produce a value needed by the following\n+  instruction. In the tournament cosim mode dmem sees random backpressure, so\n+  CoreMark pays avoidable full-pipeline bubbles on ordinary RAM stores.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts put new logic on the fetch path or tried to decouple\n+  the whole M-extension unit. A narrower backend store buffer should attack a\n+  common stall source while leaving fetch, branch resolution, RVFI width, and the\n+  working iterative divider structure unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry write buffer for aligned, non-MMIO RAM stores. When a store\n+  reaches MEM and the dmem bus is not ready, capture its address, byte mask, and\n+  replicated write data into the buffer, retire the store once architecturally\n+  enqueued, and let younger non-memory instructions continue. Drain the buffer\n+  to dmem as soon as io_dmemReady returns.\n+\n+  Preserve ordering by stalling any younger load/store while the buffer is full\n+  unless the pending store has drained, and keep UART/timing-marker MMIO stores\n+  unbuffered so CoreMark brackets and output timing remain tied to real bus\n+  acceptance. This should hide a fraction of random dmem store stalls with only\n+  a small MEM-stage register/mux addition and minimal Fmax risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry non-MMIO RAM store buffer, drain path, and RVFI-safe store enqueue semantics while keeping MMIO stores synchronous.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Change dmem stall policy so buffered stores do not freeze the pipeline, while loads, MMIO stores, and memory ops behind a full buffer still stall.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer full/drain status between MEM and hazard control without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_store_buffer.py\n+    description: \"Add cocotb coverage for stalled RAM stores, load-after-store ordering, and unbuffered MMIO marker stores.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"One-entry RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current in-order pipeline freezes behind every STORE whenever io_dmemReady\n+  is low, even though most stores do not produce a value needed by the following\n+  instruction. In the tournament cosim mode dmem sees random backpressure, so\n+  CoreMark pays avoidable full-pipeline bubbles on ordinary RAM stores.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts put new logic on the fetch path or tried to decouple\n+  the whole M-extension unit. A narrower backend store buffer should attack a\n+  common stall source while leaving fetch, branch resolution, RVFI width, and the\n+  working iterative divider structure unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry write buffer for aligned, non-MMIO RAM stores. When a store\n+  reaches MEM and the dmem bus is not ready, capture its address, byte mask, and\n+  replicated write data into the buffer, retire the store once architecturally\n+  enqueued, and let younger non-memory instructions continue. Drain the buffer\n+  to dmem as soon as io_dmemReady returns.\n+\n+  Preserve ordering by stalling any younger load/store while the buffer is full\n+  unless the pending store has drained, and keep UART/timing-marker MMIO stores\n+  unbuffered so CoreMark brackets and output timing remain tied to real bus\n+  acceptance. This should hide a fraction of random dmem store stalls with only\n+  a small MEM-stage register/mux addition and minimal Fmax risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry non-MMIO RAM store buffer, drain path, and RVFI-safe store enqueue semantics while keeping MMIO stores synchronous.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Change dmem stall policy so buffered stores do not freeze the pipeline, while loads, MMIO stores, and memory ops behind a full buffer still stall.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer full/drain status between MEM and hazard control without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_store_buffer.py\n+    description: \"Add cocotb coverage for stalled RAM stores, load-after-store ordering, and unbuffered MMIO marker stores.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n+title: \"One-entry RAM store buffer\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current in-order pipeline freezes behind every STORE whenever io_dmemReady\n+  is low, even though most stores do not produce a value needed by the following\n+  instruction. In the tournament cosim mode dmem sees random backpressure, so\n+  CoreMark pays avoidable full-pipeline bubbles on ordinary RAM stores.\n+\n+  Prior structural attempts put new logic on the fetch path or tried to decouple\n+  the whole M-extension unit. A narrower backend store buffer should attack a\n+  common stall source while leaving fetch, branch resolution, RVFI width, and the\n+  working iterative divider structure unchanged.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-entry write buffer for aligned, non-MMIO RAM stores. When a store\n+  reaches MEM and the dmem bus is not ready, capture its address, byte mask, and\n+  replicated write data into the buffer, retire the store once architecturally\n+  enqueued, and let younger non-memory instructions continue. Drain the buffer\n+  to dmem as soon as io_dmemReady returns.\n+\n+  Preserve ordering by stalling any younger load/store while the buffer is full\n+  unless the pending store has drained, and keep UART/timing-marker MMIO stores\n+  unbuffered so CoreMark brackets and output timing remain tied to real bus\n+  acceptance. This should hide a fraction of random dmem store stalls with only\n+  a small MEM-stage register/mux addition and minimal Fmax risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry non-MMIO RAM store buffer, drain path, and RVFI-safe store enqueue semantics while keeping MMIO stores synchronous.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Change dmem stall policy so buffered stores do not freeze the pipeline, while loads, MMIO stores, and memory ops behind a full buffer still stall.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire store-buffer full/drain status between MEM and hazard control without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_store_buffer.py\n+    description: \"Add cocotb coverage for stalled RAM stores, load-after-store ordering, and unbuffered MMIO marker stores.\"\n","additions":37,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778598738536,"end":1778598738540}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_006c4dad370f0fc7016a03433c5d34819391806eb951df0d5b"}},"id":"prt_e1cbea41b001PmbLFfPzlnEZok","sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","messageID":"msg_e1cbe92a60015gjfziq3gTin1C"}}
