{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778598758418,"sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_oJNMcCUhNATaubLKL87XXsGL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\n2: title: \"One-entry RAM store buffer\"\n3: category: structural\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current in-order pipeline freezes behind every STORE whenever io_dmemReady\n6:   is low, even though most stores do not produce a value needed by the following\n7:   instruction. In the tournament cosim mode dmem sees random backpressure, so\n8:   CoreMark pays avoidable full-pipeline bubbles on ordinary RAM stores.\n9: \n10:   Prior structural attempts put new logic on the fetch path or tried to decouple\n11:   the whole M-extension unit. A narrower backend store buffer should attack a\n12:   common stall source while leaving fetch, branch resolution, RVFI width, and the\n13:   working iterative divider structure unchanged.\n14: hypothesis: |\n15:   Add a one-entry write buffer for aligned, non-MMIO RAM stores. When a store\n16:   reaches MEM and the dmem bus is not ready, capture its address, byte mask, and\n17:   replicated write data into the buffer, retire the store once architecturally\n18:   enqueued, and let younger non-memory instructions continue. Drain the buffer\n19:   to dmem as soon as io_dmemReady returns.\n20: \n21:   Preserve ordering by stalling any younger load/store while the buffer is full\n22:   unless the pending store has drained, and keep UART/timing-marker MMIO stores\n23:   unbuffered so CoreMark brackets and output timing remain tied to real bus\n24:   acceptance. This should hide a fraction of random dmem store stalls with only\n25:   a small MEM-stage register/mux addition and minimal Fmax risk.\n26: expected_impact:\n27:   fitness_delta_pct: 5\n28:   confidence: medium\n29: changes:\n30:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n31:     description: \"Add a one-entry non-MMIO RAM store buffer, drain path, and RVFI-safe store enqueue semantics while keeping MMIO stores synchronous.\"\n32:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n33:     description: \"Change dmem stall policy so buffered stores do not freeze the pipeline, while loads, MMIO stores, and memory ops behind a full buffer still stall.\"\n34:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n35:     description: \"Wire store-buffer full/drain status between MEM and hazard control without changing the NRET=1 top-level IO contract.\"\n36:   - file: test/test_store_buffer.py\n37:     description: \"Add cocotb coverage for stalled RAM stores, load-after-store ordering, and unbuffered MMIO marker stores.\"\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-002-r3s1\ntitle: \"One-entry RAM store buffer\"\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The current in-order pipeline freezes behind every STORE whenever io_dmemReady\n  is low, even though most stores do not produce a value needed by the following\n  instruction. In the tournament cosim mode dmem sees random backpressure, so\n  CoreMark pays avoidable full-pipeline bubbles on ordinary RAM stores.\n\n  Prior structural attempts put new logic on the fetch path or tried to decouple\n  the whole M-extension unit. A narrower backend store buffer should attack a\n  common stall source while leaving fetch, branch resolution, RVFI width, and the\n  working iterative divider structure unchanged.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a one-entry write buffer for aligned, non-MMIO RAM stores. When a store\n  reaches MEM and the dmem bus is not ready, capture its address, byte mask, and\n  replicated write data into the buffer, retire the store once architecturally\n  enqueued, and let younger non-memory instructions continue. Drain the buffer\n  to dmem as soon as io_dmemReady returns.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r3s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778598758406,"end":1778598758417}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d5c775f0956101a016a0343658c908195b547d6fc96d9ca89"}},"id":"prt_e1cbf4518001E3mG64WbDrvTqK","sessionID":"ses_1e34495adffeLsnT1y1hqIU84t","messageID":"msg_e1cbefae0001BhkpGY4pegf3b7"}}
