{"type":"text","timestamp":1778600789543,"sessionID":"ses_1e327f826ffehBKpKYfAFfxJTs","part":{"id":"prt_e1cde3ea4001iFn54XkppRvWTo","messageID":"msg_e1cdc8178001j56TzebY62lcri","sessionID":"ses_1e327f826ffehBKpKYfAFfxJTs","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis that reuses the successful “move cold M-extension work off the common EX path” lesson, but narrows it to high-half multiply variants so CoreMark’s hot low `MUL` stays single-cycle.","time":{"start":1778600787620,"end":1778600789541},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07a77bdf3bf5c38b016a034b5375f88190848ffacca6de7884","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778600815643,"sessionID":"ses_1e327f826ffehBKpKYfAFfxJTs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_1qiDRW0AIeqFZJqdWy6sTYKu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Split high-half multiplier\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench result came from removing cold divide/remainder hardware from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path, while later attempts that added fetch\n+  queues, predictors, or store buffering lost more Fmax than they recovered in\n+  cycles. The remaining ALU still builds signed*signed, unsigned*unsigned, and\n+  signed*unsigned 64-bit multiplier cones even though CoreMark's hot path is\n+  expected to use ordinary low-half MUL far more often than MULH/MULHU/MULHSU.\n+\n+  A narrower structural split should preserve CoreMark's common single-cycle\n+  multiply behavior while removing the high-half signedness/product logic from\n+  the timing-critical EX result mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a simple single-cycle low-32-bit product, because that is the\n+  multiply form most likely used by compiled CoreMark matrix code. Move only\n+  MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU into a small iterative high-half multiply unit with\n+  the same start/done/ack discipline already proven necessary for the divider.\n+\n+  In the core build, EX should treat the high-half multiply variants like the\n+  existing iterative divider: hold ID/EX while the unit runs, latch the original\n+  forwarded operands for RVFI, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result when done.\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the substituted algebraic results on the\n+  existing one-cycle ALU path so formal remains tractable and aligned with the\n+  riscv-formal altops spec. This should reduce the non-ALTOPS FPGA multiplier\n+  routing/mux cone without adding fetch-path or memory-ordering control.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Keep low-half MUL single-cycle, preserve ALTOPS behavior, and remove/prune real high-half multiplier products from the core's common ALU path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mulh_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an iterative RV32M-correct high-half multiply unit for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with signedness handling and done/ack result hold semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route MULH-family operations through mulh_unit, freeze the pipeline via the existing busy path, retain forwarded operands for RVFI, and release one EX/MEM result on completion.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mulh_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add edge-case cocotb vectors for the new high-half multiplier unit so RV32M signedness and corner cases remain checked after the structural split.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Split high-half multiplier\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench result came from removing cold divide/remainder hardware from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path, while later attempts that added fetch\n+  queues, predictors, or store buffering lost more Fmax than they recovered in\n+  cycles. The remaining ALU still builds signed*signed, unsigned*unsigned, and\n+  signed*unsigned 64-bit multiplier cones even though CoreMark's hot path is\n+  expected to use ordinary low-half MUL far more often than MULH/MULHU/MULHSU.\n+\n+  A narrower structural split should preserve CoreMark's common single-cycle\n+  multiply behavior while removing the high-half signedness/product logic from\n+  the timing-critical EX result mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a simple single-cycle low-32-bit product, because that is the\n+  multiply form most likely used by compiled CoreMark matrix code. Move only\n+  MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU into a small iterative high-half multiply unit with\n+  the same start/done/ack discipline already proven necessary for the divider.\n+\n+  In the core build, EX should treat the high-half multiply variants like the\n+  existing iterative divider: hold ID/EX while the unit runs, latch the original\n+  forwarded operands for RVFI, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result when done.\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the substituted algebraic results on the\n+  existing one-cycle ALU path so formal remains tractable and aligned with the\n+  riscv-formal altops spec. This should reduce the non-ALTOPS FPGA multiplier\n+  routing/mux cone without adding fetch-path or memory-ordering control.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Keep low-half MUL single-cycle, preserve ALTOPS behavior, and remove/prune real high-half multiplier products from the core's common ALU path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mulh_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an iterative RV32M-correct high-half multiply unit for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with signedness handling and done/ack result hold semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route MULH-family operations through mulh_unit, freeze the pipeline via the existing busy path, retain forwarded operands for RVFI, and release one EX/MEM result on completion.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mulh_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add edge-case cocotb vectors for the new high-half multiplier unit so RV32M signedness and corner cases remain checked after the structural split.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r4s1\n+title: \"Split high-half multiplier\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best bench result came from removing cold divide/remainder hardware from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path, while later attempts that added fetch\n+  queues, predictors, or store buffering lost more Fmax than they recovered in\n+  cycles. The remaining ALU still builds signed*signed, unsigned*unsigned, and\n+  signed*unsigned 64-bit multiplier cones even though CoreMark's hot path is\n+  expected to use ordinary low-half MUL far more often than MULH/MULHU/MULHSU.\n+\n+  A narrower structural split should preserve CoreMark's common single-cycle\n+  multiply behavior while removing the high-half signedness/product logic from\n+  the timing-critical EX result mux.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep ALU_MUL as a simple single-cycle low-32-bit product, because that is the\n+  multiply form most likely used by compiled CoreMark matrix code. Move only\n+  MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU into a small iterative high-half multiply unit with\n+  the same start/done/ack discipline already proven necessary for the divider.\n+\n+  In the core build, EX should treat the high-half multiply variants like the\n+  existing iterative divider: hold ID/EX while the unit runs, latch the original\n+  forwarded operands for RVFI, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result when done.\n+  Under RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the substituted algebraic results on the\n+  existing one-cycle ALU path so formal remains tractable and aligned with the\n+  riscv-formal altops spec. This should reduce the non-ALTOPS FPGA multiplier\n+  routing/mux cone without adding fetch-path or memory-ordering control.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 6\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Keep low-half MUL single-cycle, preserve ALTOPS behavior, and remove/prune real high-half multiplier products from the core's common ALU path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mulh_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an iterative RV32M-correct high-half multiply unit for MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU with signedness handling and done/ack result hold semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Route MULH-family operations through mulh_unit, freeze the pipeline via the existing busy path, retain forwarded operands for RVFI, and release one EX/MEM result on completion.\"\n+  - file: test/test_mulh_unit.py\n+    description: \"Add edge-case cocotb vectors for the new high-half multiplier unit so RV32M signedness and corner cases remain checked after the structural split.\"\n","additions":39,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r4s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778600815639,"end":1778600815642}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07a77bdf3bf5c38b016a034b55742c8190b4c4762a7217812f"}},"id":"prt_e1cde4627001P0lRxB3hJ6T4yk