{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778602433540,"sessionID":"ses_1e30c49b6ffe3HngQXbTssxUx1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_elNHnpzD3iDYtiNchtbuUC7P","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\n+title: Pipelined full multiplier unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\n+  single-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\n+  in the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\n+  stores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\n+  that common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\n+  two-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products followed\n+  by a registered combine/sign-select stage. EX should treat every real multiply\n+  like the existing iterative divider: latch the forwarded operands, assert a\n+  busy stall while the unit is active, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result with the\n+  original operands preserved for RVFI.\n+\n+  This pays one extra cycle on CoreMark multiply instructions, but it removes the\n+  32x32/64-bit product cone from the common single-cycle RV32I execute path and\n+  should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than the modest MUL CPI loss. Under\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\n+  the formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: Remove real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving the existing ALTOPS substitutions.\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: Add a dedicated two-cycle RV32M multiplier using registered 16x16 partial products, signedness control, start/done/ack, and stable result holding.\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: Route all real multiply ops through mul_unit, share the existing execute-busy stall pattern with div_unit, and preserve latched operands for RVFI.\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: Keep the ex_busy pipeline freeze correct for multiply busy cycles and ensure one result is retired without duplicate starts.\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: Move or extend RV32M multiply vectors so the new mul_unit path, not the stripped ALU fallback, is checked for exact RV32M results.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\n+title: Pipelined full multiplier unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\n+  single-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\n+  in the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\n+  stores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\n+  that common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\n+  two-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products followed\n+  by a registered combine/sign-select stage. EX should treat every real multiply\n+  like the existing iterative divider: latch the forwarded operands, assert a\n+  busy stall while the unit is active, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result with the\n+  original operands preserved for RVFI.\n+\n+  This pays one extra cycle on CoreMark multiply instructions, but it removes the\n+  32x32/64-bit product cone from the common single-cycle RV32I execute path and\n+  should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than the modest MUL CPI loss. Under\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\n+  the formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: Remove real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving the existing ALTOPS substitutions.\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: Add a dedicated two-cycle RV32M multiplier using registered 16x16 partial products, signedness control, start/done/ack, and stable result holding.\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: Route all real multiply ops through mul_unit, share the existing execute-busy stall pattern with div_unit, and preserve latched operands for RVFI.\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: Keep the ex_busy pipeline freeze correct for multiply busy cycles and ensure one result is retired without duplicate starts.\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: Move or extend RV32M multiply vectors so the new mul_unit path, not the stripped ALU fallback, is checked for exact RV32M results.\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\n+title: Pipelined full multiplier unit\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\n+  the common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\n+  single-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\n+  in the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\n+  stores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\n+  that common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\n+  two-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products followed\n+  by a registered combine/sign-select stage. EX should treat every real multiply\n+  like the existing iterative divider: latch the forwarded operands, assert a\n+  busy stall while the unit is active, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result with the\n+  original operands preserved for RVFI.\n+\n+  This pays one extra cycle on CoreMark multiply instructions, but it removes the\n+  32x32/64-bit product cone from the common single-cycle RV32I execute path and\n+  should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than the modest MUL CPI loss. Under\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\n+  the formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: Remove real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving the existing ALTOPS substitutions.\n+  - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n+    description: Add a dedicated two-cycle RV32M multiplier using registered 16x16 partial products, signedness control, start/done/ack, and stable result holding.\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: Route all real multiply ops through mul_unit, share the existing execute-busy stall pattern with div_unit, and preserve latched operands for RVFI.\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: Keep the ex_busy pipeline freeze correct for multiply busy cycles and ensure one result is retired without duplicate starts.\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: Move or extend RV32M multiply vectors so the new mul_unit path, not the stripped ALU fallback, is checked for exact RV32M results.\n","additions":37,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r5s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778602433537,"end":1778602433539}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_082f4ef4abc995c5016a0351aa4410819693f06bb641dec654"}},"id":"prt_e1cf701aa0011Qfgdm3ukC3X0M","sessionID":"ses_1e30c49b6ffe3HngQXbTssxUx1","messageID":"msg_e1cf646780011fm4Wf8Gt1cUTo"}}
