e existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\n23:   the formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\n24: expected_impact:\n25:   fitness_delta_pct: 5\n26:   confidence: medium\n27: changes:\n28:   - file: rtl/alu.sv\n29:     description: Remove real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU product generation from the common ALU path while preserving the existing ALTOPS substitutions.\n30:   - file: rtl/mul_unit.sv\n31:     description: Add a dedicated two-cycle RV32M multiplier using registered 16x16 partial products, signedness control, start/done/ack, and stable result holding.\n32:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n33:     description: Route all real multiply ops through mul_unit, share the existing execute-busy stall pattern with div_unit, and preserve latched operands for RVFI.\n34:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n35:     description: Keep the ex_busy pipeline freeze correct for multiply busy cycles and ensure one result is retired without duplicate starts.\n36:   - file: test/test_alu.py\n37:     description: Move or extend RV32M multiply vectors so the new mul_unit path, not the stripped ALU fallback, is checked for exact RV32M results.\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\ntitle: Pipelined full multiplier unit\ncategory: structural\nmotivation: |\n  The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\n  the common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\n  single-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\n  in the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\n  stores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\n  that common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\nhypothesis: |\n  Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\n  two-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products