{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778606916906,"sessionID":"ses_1e2c4ec66ffeomAFIxBSpr6bYE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EzID8TjiptPJ1Ndr9nLcvxjG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","offset":15,"limit":1},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n15: {\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\", \"title\": \"Pipelined full multiplier unit\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\\nthe common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\\nsingle-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\\nin the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\\nstores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\\nthat common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\\nthe common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\\nsingle-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\\nin the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\\nstores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\\nthat common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\\ntwo-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products followed\\nby a registered combine/sign-select stage. EX should treat every real multiply\\nlike the existing iterative divider: latch the forwarded operands, assert a\\nbusy stall while the unit is active, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result with the\\noriginal operands preserved for RVFI.\\n\\nThis pays one extra cycle on CoreMark multiply instructions, but it removes the\\n32x32/64-bit product cone from the common single-cycle RV32I execute path and\\nshould improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than the modest MUL CPI loss. Under\\nRISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\\nthe formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Showing lines 15-15 of 22. Use offset=16 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"id\": \"hyp-20260512-002-r5s1\", \"title\": \"Pipelined full multiplier unit\", \"category\": \"structural\", \"motivation\": \"The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\\nthe common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\\nsingle-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\\nin the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\\nstores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\\nthat common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": {\"motivation\": \"The best measured improvement came from removing cold divide/remainder logic from\\nthe common execute-stage ALU path. The remaining wide arithmetic limiter is the\\nsingle-cycle RV32M multiplier cone: the ALU still builds multiple 64-bit products\\nin the same result path used by ordinary adds, branches, address generation, and\\nstores. Prior high-half-only attempts regressed because low-half MUL stayed in\\nthat common cone, so the critical path was not structurally removed.\\n\", \"hypothesis\": \"Move all real MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU execution out of rtl/alu.sv into a dedicated\\ntwo-cycle multiplier unit built from registered 16x16 partial products followed\\nby a registered combine/sign-select stage. EX should treat every real multiply\\nlike the existing iterative divider: latch the forwarded operands, assert a\\nbusy stall while the unit is active, and emit exactly one EX/MEM result with the\\noriginal operands preserved for RVFI.\\n\\nThis pays one extra cycle on CoreMark multiply instructions, but it removes the\\n32x32/64-bit product cone from the common single-cycle RV32I execute path and\\nshould improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax more than the modest MUL CPI loss. Under\\nRISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS, keep the existing algebraic substitutions single-cycle so\\nthe formal harness remains tractable and consistent with the spec files.\\n\", \"expected_impact\": {\"fitness_delta_pct\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/log.jsonl","time":{"start":1778606916898,"end":1778606916905}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0086a67bce868276016a036344bf8881959218dafb1391efe5"}},"id":"prt_e1d3bc500001ZHfDkq60DZsknj","sessionID":"ses_1e2c4ec66ffeomAFIxBSpr6bYE","messageID":"msg_e1d3b7740001kyJjumnnqUszn2"}}
