{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778608996761,"sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c2d8ffehL79cZNwJ6IJ5n","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_G1v9OIat6iKSmQqlyeahmnOv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Registered writeback result path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent winning changes improved fitness by removing late pipeline baggage\n+  rather than adding predictors, queues, or buffers. The current MEM/WB stage\n+  still carries both alu_result and read_data plus a mem_to_reg control bit,\n+  then rebuilds the final writeback value through a combinational mux in WB.\n+  That mux output fans out to the register file, MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding, and\n+  RVFI rd_wdata, so it can sit on the common dependent-instruction path even\n+  though the load-versus-ALU choice is already known when MEM/WB captures.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move final writeback-value selection into the MEM stage and store a single\n+  registered wb_data field in MEM/WB. Remove the separate MEM/WB read_data,\n+  alu_result, and mem_to_reg payload/control used only to recreate that value\n+  one cycle later, and make wb_stage a simple valid/reg_write gate around the\n+  registered result.\n+\n+  This keeps pipeline timing, NRET=1 RVFI behavior, memory ordering, dmem-stall\n+  hold semantics, and CoreMark instruction count unchanged while shortening the\n+  MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding cone and trimming one 32-bit late-stage payload. The\n+  change follows the successful control-pruning direction but avoids the r8s0\n+  mistake of increasing store-data fanout, because it only collapses mutually\n+  exclusive writeback-result copies after MEM has already consumed them.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace MEM/WB alu_result/read_data plus mem_to_reg with a single wb_data payload and narrower writeback control.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and register the final writeback value at the MEM/WB boundary while preserving load extension, RVFI memory fields, and hold_wb forwarding semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive register-file write data directly from the registered MEM/WB wb_data field, leaving only valid and reg_write gating in WB.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r9s1\n+title: \"Registered writeback result path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent winning changes improved fitness by removing late pipeline baggage\n+  rather than adding predictors, queues, or buffers. The current MEM/WB stage\n+  still carries both alu_result and read_data plus a mem_to_reg control bit,\n+  then rebuilds the final writeback value through a combinational mux in WB.\n+  That mux output fans out to the register file, MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding, and\n+  RVFI rd_wdata, so it can sit on the common dependent-instruction path even\n+  though the load-versus-ALU choice is already known when MEM/WB captures.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Move final writeback-value selection into the MEM stage and store a single\n+  registered wb_data field in MEM/WB. Remove the separate MEM/WB read_data,\n+  alu_result, and mem_to_reg payload/control used only to recreate that value\n+  one cycle later, and make wb_stage a simple valid/reg_write gate around the\n+  registered result.\n+\n+  This keeps pipeline timing, NRET=1 RVFI behavior, memory ordering, dmem-stall\n+  hold semantics, and CoreMark instruction count unchanged while shortening the\n+  MEM/WB-to-EX forwarding cone and trimming one 32-bit late-stage payload. The\n+  change follows the successful control-pruning direction but avoids the r8s0\n+  mistake of increasing store-data fanout, because it only collapses mutually\n+  exclusive writeback-result copies after MEM has already consumed them.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace MEM/WB alu_result/read_data plus mem_to_reg with a single wb_data payload and narrower writeback control.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute and register the final writeback value at the MEM/WB boundary while preserving load extension, RVFI memory fields, and hold_wb forwarding semantics.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive register-file write data directly from the registered MEM/WB wb_data field, leaving only valid and reg_write gating in WB.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r9s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhig