{"type":"text","timestamp":1778610518158,"sessionID":"ses_1e292bc96ffeAG62aE3Q2RW4S8","part":{"id":"prt_e1d72b1cc001GCslMBma9m376e","messageID":"msg_e1d71d1e5001Vhp9k23lzBESzv","sessionID":"ses_1e292bc96ffeAG62aE3Q2RW4S8","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as an instruction-fetch value predictor rather than another branch-target predictor: it targets the random iStall component and leaves the branch PC path/repair machinery out of scope.","time":{"start":1778610516428,"end":1778610518152},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c36f5179ee17a4d016a03715453388197ae41b6a5c91c1750","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778610538317,"sessionID":"ses_1e292bc96ffeAG62aE3Q2RW4S8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_GA6VRZKmuu0XSd2hqHcbmzJm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Tiny ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior branch predictors for this core consistently regressed because they put\n+  target lookup, instruction predecode, prediction metadata, or repair muxing on\n+  the shallow fetch/redirect path. The apples-to-apples CoreMark mode also has\n+  roughly 22% random instruction-bus stalls, and the current frontend turns every\n+  low io_imemReady cycle into a NOP even when the same hot-loop PC was fetched\n+  correctly on an earlier iteration.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped instruction replay predictor trained only by accepted\n+  instruction fetches. On an io_imemReady=1 fetch, record {PC tag, instruction}\n+  in an 8-entry table. On a later io_imemReady=0 cycle, if the current PC hits\n+  the table, supply the cached instruction and treat fetch as effectively ready;\n+  otherwise keep the existing stall/NOP behavior.\n+\n+  This is not a branch target predictor and does not carry prediction metadata\n+  into EX. It attacks repeated hot-loop iStalls while avoiding the failed IF\n+  branch-predecode/BTB/RAS/backedge-repair paths. Because the instruction memory\n+  is immutable in FPGA/cosim and formal ties io_imemReady high, a replay hit is\n+  architecturally the same instruction word previously observed for that PC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an 8-entry PC-tagged instruction replay predictor, fill it on accepted ready fetches, and output cached instructions on stalled tag hits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF-stage effective-fetch-ready signal into the existing hazard path while preserving the NRET=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat replay hits as instruction-fetch ready for stall/flush decisions, falling back to the current imem-stall behavior on predictor misses.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Tiny ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior branch predictors for this core consistently regressed because they put\n+  target lookup, instruction predecode, prediction metadata, or repair muxing on\n+  the shallow fetch/redirect path. The apples-to-apples CoreMark mode also has\n+  roughly 22% random instruction-bus stalls, and the current frontend turns every\n+  low io_imemReady cycle into a NOP even when the same hot-loop PC was fetched\n+  correctly on an earlier iteration.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped instruction replay predictor trained only by accepted\n+  instruction fetches. On an io_imemReady=1 fetch, record {PC tag, instruction}\n+  in an 8-entry table. On a later io_imemReady=0 cycle, if the current PC hits\n+  the table, supply the cached instruction and treat fetch as effectively ready;\n+  otherwise keep the existing stall/NOP behavior.\n+\n+  This is not a branch target predictor and does not carry prediction metadata\n+  into EX. It attacks repeated hot-loop iStalls while avoiding the failed IF\n+  branch-predecode/BTB/RAS/backedge-repair paths. Because the instruction memory\n+  is immutable in FPGA/cosim and formal ties io_imemReady high, a replay hit is\n+  architecturally the same instruction word previously observed for that PC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an 8-entry PC-tagged instruction replay predictor, fill it on accepted ready fetches, and output cached instructions on stalled tag hits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF-stage effective-fetch-ready signal into the existing hazard path while preserving the NRET=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat replay hits as instruction-fetch ready for stall/flush decisions, falling back to the current imem-stall behavior on predictor misses.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r10s2\n+title: \"Tiny ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior branch predictors for this core consistently regressed because they put\n+  target lookup, instruction predecode, prediction metadata, or repair muxing on\n+  the shallow fetch/redirect path. The apples-to-apples CoreMark mode also has\n+  roughly 22% random instruction-bus stalls, and the current frontend turns every\n+  low io_imemReady cycle into a NOP even when the same hot-loop PC was fetched\n+  correctly on an earlier iteration.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny direct-mapped instruction replay predictor trained only by accepted\n+  instruction fetches. On an io_imemReady=1 fetch, record {PC tag, instruction}\n+  in an 8-entry table. On a later io_imemReady=0 cycle, if the current PC hits\n+  the table, supply the cached instruction and treat fetch as effectively ready;\n+  otherwise keep the existing stall/NOP behavior.\n+\n+  This is not a branch target predictor and does not carry prediction metadata\n+  into EX. It attacks repeated hot-loop iStalls while avoiding the failed IF\n+  branch-predecode/BTB/RAS/backedge-repair paths. Because the instruction memory\n+  is immutable in FPGA/cosim and formal ties io_imemReady high, a replay hit is\n+  architecturally the same instruction word previously observed for that PC.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add an 8-entry PC-tagged instruction replay predictor, fill it on accepted ready fetches, and output cached instructions on stalled tag hits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the IF-stage effective-fetch-ready signal into the existing hazard path while preserving the NRET=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Treat replay hits as instruction-fetch ready for stall/flush decisions, falling back to the current imem-stall behavior on predictor misses.\"\n","additions":32,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r10s2.yam