{"type":"text","timestamp":1778611648666,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d172bffeynDzXGaMaO3H9c","part":{"id":"prt_e1d83f4670017sgRrifPcbJMPf","messageID":"msg_e1d8354f7001IuFbBbXXgeC7MR","sessionID":"ses_1e27d172bffeynDzXGaMaO3H9c","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently lost by adding branch-target prediction or repair metadata; the only predictor win was the existing fetch replay table. I’m going to propose a narrow follow-on: increase replay coverage without introducing branch prediction state or EX repair paths.","time":{"start":1778611647591,"end":1778611648665},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a8196a122e124ed016a0375bf7cfc8195a81291ece1b12541","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778611663971,"sessionID":"ses_1e27d172bffeynDzXGaMaO3H9c","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_4e8K98PP2GFPdSXVzwR2U83R","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\n+title: Wider ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only successful predictor result so far was the tiny instruction-fetch\n+  replay table, because it converts random hot-loop instruction-bus stalls into\n+  useful decode cycles without adding branch target lookup, prediction repair,\n+  or EX-stage metadata. CoreMark's timed working set is larger than eight\n+  fetch-table slots, so direct-mapped conflicts can still turn repeated PCs\n+  back into imem stalls even after warmup.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Expand the IF-stage instruction replay predictor from 8 direct-mapped entries\n+  to 16 direct-mapped entries while keeping the exact same training and use\n+  discipline: fill only on accepted io_imemReady fetches, replay only when\n+  io_imemReady is low and the current PC tag hits, and leave all branch/jump\n+  prediction behavior unchanged. This should reduce replay conflict misses in\n+  CoreMark hot loops under the 22% random iStall model while avoiding the\n+  target-PC muxing and prediction-repair metadata that made earlier branch\n+  predictors regress. The added hardware is one more index bit and a modestly\n+  larger tag/instruction array, so the expected gain is smaller than the first\n+  replay predictor but still plausible.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Increase the PC-tagged instruction replay predictor to 16 direct-mapped entries, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\n+title: Wider ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only successful predictor result so far was the tiny instruction-fetch\n+  replay table, because it converts random hot-loop instruction-bus stalls into\n+  useful decode cycles without adding branch target lookup, prediction repair,\n+  or EX-stage metadata. CoreMark's timed working set is larger than eight\n+  fetch-table slots, so direct-mapped conflicts can still turn repeated PCs\n+  back into imem stalls even after warmup.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Expand the IF-stage instruction replay predictor from 8 direct-mapped entries\n+  to 16 direct-mapped entries while keeping the exact same training and use\n+  discipline: fill only on accepted io_imemReady fetches, replay only when\n+  io_imemReady is low and the current PC tag hits, and leave all branch/jump\n+  prediction behavior unchanged. This should reduce replay conflict misses in\n+  CoreMark hot loops under the 22% random iStall model while avoiding the\n+  target-PC muxing and prediction-repair metadata that made earlier branch\n+  predictors regress. The added hardware is one more index bit and a modestly\n+  larger tag/instruction array, so the expected gain is smaller than the first\n+  replay predictor but still plausible.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Increase the PC-tagged instruction replay predictor to 16 direct-mapped entries, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall semantics.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r11s2\n+title: Wider ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only successful predictor result so far was the tiny instruction-fetch\n+  replay table, because it converts random hot-loop instruction-bus stalls into\n+  useful decode cycles without adding branch target lookup, prediction repair,\n+  or EX-stage metadata. CoreMark's timed working set is larger than eight\n+  fetch-table slots, so direct-mapped conflicts can still turn repeated PCs\n+  back into imem stalls even after warmup.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Expand the IF-stage instruction replay predictor from 8 direct-mapped entries\n+  to 16 direct-mapped entries while keeping the exact same training and use\n+  discipline: fill only on accepted io_imemReady fetches, replay only when\n+  io_imemReady is low and the current PC tag hits, and leave all branch/jump\n+  prediction behavior unchanged. This should reduce replay conflict misses in\n+  CoreMark hot loops under the 22% random iStall model while avoiding the\n+  target-PC muxing and prediction-repair metadata that made earlier branch\n+  predictors regress. The added hardware is one more index bit and a modestly\n+  larger tag/instruction array, so the expected gain is smaller than the first\n+  replay predictor but still plausible.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Increase the PC-tagged instruction replay predictor to 16 direct-mapped entries, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall semantics.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r11s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778611663962,"end":1778611663970}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0a8196a122e124ed016a0375c093788195988932092f45c00c"}},"id":"prt_e1d83f89a001yMtsjN4y8ocVMm","sessionID":"ses_1e27d172bffeynDzXGaMaO3H9c","messageID":"msg_e1d8354f7001IuFbBbXXgeC7MR"}}
