{"type":"text","timestamp":1778612602455,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f7626ffejOu5nu2jJTJ687","part":{"id":"prt_e1d927e70001UWY0bG3Ui8bR1W","messageID":"msg_e1d915b60001bCwx1fTSRf4DhT","sessionID":"ses_1e26f7626ffejOu5nu2jJTJ687","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as a single `if_stage.sv` change: repack the existing 8-word replay predictor into 4 two-word cache lines with per-word valid bits, aiming to preserve the winning replay behavior while reducing tag compare/storage routing.","time":{"start":1778612600432,"end":1778612602454},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ea58d2f726a189f016a0379784db88196b2c6ce7f981165e7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778612618866,"sessionID":"ses_1e26f7626ffejOu5nu2jJTJ687","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_jljmZWrpbSGmhM0jZ0bOtAUx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: Line-packed ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that improved this bench core was the tiny instruction-fetch replay table, which converts random hot-loop iStall cycles into useful decoded instructions without branch target prediction or EX repair metadata. Follow-up attempts to widen the table or remove payload resets regressed, suggesting the remaining replay cost is tag/control routing rather than capacity or reset muxing.\n+\n+  A predictor refinement should therefore keep the accepted-fetch-only replay semantics but reduce the fetch-stage compare and tag storage pressure that now sits on every stalled fetch decision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Repack the current 8-entry single-word replay table into four two-word replay lines. Each line stores one full PC tag, two instruction words, and per-word valid bits; accepted fetches fill only the addressed half, clearing the sibling valid bit when a different tag replaces the line. On io_imemReady=0, a replay hit still requires a full tag match plus the selected half valid bit, then supplies the cached immutable instruction and asserts imem_effective_ready exactly as today.\n+\n+  This preserves the successful no-branch-prediction replay model and the NRET=1 RVFI contract while halving the number of stored tags and tag-select routing. CoreMark loops are mostly sequential within short basic blocks, so pairing adjacent instructions should keep most of the replay hit-rate benefit while modestly improving Fmax versus the current per-word tag table.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the 8 single-word replay entries with four two-word line entries using one full tag per line and per-half valid bits, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: Line-packed ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that improved this bench core was the tiny instruction-fetch replay table, which converts random hot-loop iStall cycles into useful decoded instructions without branch target prediction or EX repair metadata. Follow-up attempts to widen the table or remove payload resets regressed, suggesting the remaining replay cost is tag/control routing rather than capacity or reset muxing.\n+\n+  A predictor refinement should therefore keep the accepted-fetch-only replay semantics but reduce the fetch-stage compare and tag storage pressure that now sits on every stalled fetch decision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Repack the current 8-entry single-word replay table into four two-word replay lines. Each line stores one full PC tag, two instruction words, and per-word valid bits; accepted fetches fill only the addressed half, clearing the sibling valid bit when a different tag replaces the line. On io_imemReady=0, a replay hit still requires a full tag match plus the selected half valid bit, then supplies the cached immutable instruction and asserts imem_effective_ready exactly as today.\n+\n+  This preserves the successful no-branch-prediction replay model and the NRET=1 RVFI contract while halving the number of stored tags and tag-select routing. CoreMark loops are mostly sequential within short basic blocks, so pairing adjacent instructions should keep most of the replay hit-rate benefit while modestly improving Fmax versus the current per-word tag table.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the 8 single-word replay entries with four two-word line entries using one full tag per line and per-half valid bits, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r12s2\n+title: Line-packed ifetch replay predictor\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that improved this bench core was the tiny instruction-fetch replay table, which converts random hot-loop iStall cycles into useful decoded instructions without branch target prediction or EX repair metadata. Follow-up attempts to widen the table or remove payload resets regressed, suggesting the remaining replay cost is tag/control routing rather than capacity or reset muxing.\n+\n+  A predictor refinement should therefore keep the accepted-fetch-only replay semantics but reduce the fetch-stage compare and tag storage pressure that now sits on every stalled fetch decision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Repack the current 8-entry single-word replay table into four two-word replay lines. Each line stores one full PC tag, two instruction words, and per-word valid bits; accepted fetches fill only the addressed half, clearing the sibling valid bit when a different tag replaces the line. On io_imemReady=0, a replay hit still requires a full tag match plus the selected half valid bit, then supplies the cached immutable instruction and asserts imem_effective_ready exactly as today.\n+\n+  This preserves the successful no-branch-prediction replay model and the NRET=1 RVFI contract while halving the number of stored tags and tag-select routing. CoreMark loops are mostly sequential within short basic blocks, so pairing adjacent instructions should keep most of the replay hit-rate benefit while modestly improving Fmax versus the current per-word tag table.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the 8 single-word replay entries with four two-word line entries using one full tag per line and per-half valid bits, preserving fill-on-ready and replay-on-stall behavior.\"\n","additions":17,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r12s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778612618857,"end":1778612618864}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ea58d2f726a189f016a03797a5fcc819688fdbb564dbd7e82"}},"id":"prt_e1d928657002NHsdMBKXUj3l1U","sessionID":"ses_1e26f7626ffejOu5nu2jJTJ687","messageID":"msg_e1d915b60001bCwx1fTSRf4DhT"}}
