{"type":"text","timestamp":1778614495569,"sessionID":"ses_1e2547587ffer0J8SK97dtlKCz","part":{"id":"prt_e1daf690f001XB4q1IHAo1pmJO","messageID":"msg_e1dadf746001qBNvr6LJRQwcqN","sessionID":"ses_1e2547587ffer0J8SK97dtlKCz","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a minimal predictor hypothesis that keeps the successful replay lookup path intact and only filters replay-table training to avoid redirect-cycle wrong-path pollution.","time":{"start":1778614495503,"end":1778614495568},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_00a784a9211acfc3016a0380df613c819390bf7e12a52a9da7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778614513782,"sessionID":"ses_1e2547587ffer0J8SK97dtlKCz","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_dXOFjx9VaGxF6W9Ugv5lWRoM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Redirect-filtered replay training\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that has improved this core is the tiny accepted-fetch\n+  instruction replay table, because it hides random hot-loop iStalls without\n+  adding branch target lookup or EX repair metadata. The current IF code still\n+  fills the direct-mapped replay entry on any io_imemReady cycle, including the\n+  cycle an EX redirect kills the fetched sequential wrong-path instruction.\n+  In tight taken loops, those wrong-path fall-through fills can repeatedly\n+  evict useful loop-body replay entries with the same pc[4:2] index.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing 8-entry replay predictor lookup and hit semantics exactly\n+  as they are, but train the table only when the fetched instruction is not\n+  being killed by a redirect/flush. On an EX redirect, update the architectural\n+  PC to the target as today but skip the replay fill for the wrong-path word at\n+  the old PC. If that fall-through path is later executed for real, it will be\n+  fetched and trained on a non-redirect cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve replay hit quality for CoreMark's repeated taken loops\n+  without adding a new IF tag compare, target mux, branch predecode path, or\n+  prediction metadata. The change is intentionally small: it may recover a few\n+  iStall bubbles by reducing direct-mapped pollution while preserving Fmax and\n+  all NRET=1 RVFI behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate replay-table fills during redirect/flush-killed fetches so wrong-path instructions do not overwrite hot-loop replay entries; preserve existing replay-hit and PC-update behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Redirect-filtered replay training\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that has improved this core is the tiny accepted-fetch\n+  instruction replay table, because it hides random hot-loop iStalls without\n+  adding branch target lookup or EX repair metadata. The current IF code still\n+  fills the direct-mapped replay entry on any io_imemReady cycle, including the\n+  cycle an EX redirect kills the fetched sequential wrong-path instruction.\n+  In tight taken loops, those wrong-path fall-through fills can repeatedly\n+  evict useful loop-body replay entries with the same pc[4:2] index.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing 8-entry replay predictor lookup and hit semantics exactly\n+  as they are, but train the table only when the fetched instruction is not\n+  being killed by a redirect/flush. On an EX redirect, update the architectural\n+  PC to the target as today but skip the replay fill for the wrong-path word at\n+  the old PC. If that fall-through path is later executed for real, it will be\n+  fetched and trained on a non-redirect cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve replay hit quality for CoreMark's repeated taken loops\n+  without adding a new IF tag compare, target mux, branch predecode path, or\n+  prediction metadata. The change is intentionally small: it may recover a few\n+  iStall bubbles by reducing direct-mapped pollution while preserving Fmax and\n+  all NRET=1 RVFI behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate replay-table fills during redirect/flush-killed fetches so wrong-path instructions do not overwrite hot-loop replay entries; preserve existing replay-hit and PC-update behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Redirect-filtered replay training\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that has improved this core is the tiny accepted-fetch\n+  instruction replay table, because it hides random hot-loop iStalls without\n+  adding branch target lookup or EX repair metadata. The current IF code still\n+  fills the direct-mapped replay entry on any io_imemReady cycle, including the\n+  cycle an EX redirect kills the fetched sequential wrong-path instruction.\n+  In tight taken loops, those wrong-path fall-through fills can repeatedly\n+  evict useful loop-body replay entries with the same pc[4:2] index.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing 8-entry replay predictor lookup and hit semantics exactly\n+  as they are, but train the table only when the fetched instruction is not\n+  being killed by a redirect/flush. On an EX redirect, update the architectural\n+  PC to the target as today but skip the replay fill for the wrong-path word at\n+  the old PC. If that fall-through path is later executed for real, it will be\n+  fetched and trained on a non-redirect cycle.\n+\n+  This should improve replay hit quality for CoreMark's repeated taken loops\n+  without adding a new IF tag compare, target mux, branch predecode path, or\n+  prediction metadata. The change is intentionally small: it may recover a few\n+  iStall bubbles by reducing direct-mapped pollution while preserving Fmax and\n+  all NRET=1 RVFI behavior.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Gate replay-table fills during redirect/flush-killed fetches so wrong-path instructions do not overwrite hot-loop replay entries; preserve existing replay-hit and PC-update behavior.\"\n","additions":30,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r13s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778614513778,"end":1778614513781}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_00a784a9211acfc3016a0380df7bcc81938e7840663d1d0c5f"}},"id":"prt_e1daf6952001mPkhCp47xSjGMV","sessionID":"ses_1e2547587ffer0J8SK97dtlKCz","messageID":"msg_e1dadf746001qBNvr6LJRQwcqN"}}
