{"type":"text","timestamp":1778615828483,"sessionID":"ses_1e23d072affeiVe1OxOaRo7RM8","part":{"id":"prt_e1dc3bf4f001kuDNm9XUsa2VDs","messageID":"msg_e1dc34740001AvzGBVSovksphX","sessionID":"ses_1e23d072affeiVe1OxOaRo7RM8","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a small replay-predictor indexing hypothesis: no branch target prediction, no EX metadata, and only one `if_stage.sv` change to reduce direct-mapped replay conflicts with a folded PC index.","time":{"start":1778615828303,"end":1778615828482},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_065c0162c79f0ddf016a038614310481958a5180a0fb5fa1ff","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778615837575,"sessionID":"ses_1e23d072affeiVe1OxOaRo7RM8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Gw5eGkWmGG3rSyaT7azxSjbk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Folded-index ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that has produced a large bench improvement is the accepted-fetch instruction replay table, because it hides random hot-loop iStalls without branch-target lookup, predecode, or EX repair metadata. Follow-up replay changes that widened the table, repacked lines, warmed during backend stalls, or filtered redirect fills all regressed, so the next predictor step should preserve the same simple lookup semantics and avoid adding new storage depth or control paths.\n+\n+  The current 8-entry table is indexed directly by pc[4:2], so instructions separated by 32-byte strides always evict each other. CoreMark loop bodies and call-heavy code can easily contain hot PCs with that spacing, causing replay misses even after each instruction has been fetched successfully before.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the 8-entry accepted-fetch replay predictor exactly the same size and keep its fill-on-io_imemReady, replay-only-when-io_imemReady-is-low semantics, but replace the direct pc[4:2] index with a cheap folded hash such as pc[4:2] ^ pc[7:5]. Keep the existing full replay tag comparison so replay hits remain exact for the immutable instruction memory contract.\n+\n+  This targets direct-mapped conflict misses without the larger array, half-line muxing, backend warm cursor, redirect filter, branch predictor metadata, or next-PC target muxes that hurt prior predictor attempts. The hardware cost is only a few XOR gates feeding the existing 3-bit replay index, so any recovered hot-loop iStall hits should have a better chance of improving CoreMark fitness than another branch predictor or wider replay cache.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change the replay table index from direct pc[4:2] to a small folded PC hash while preserving the 8-entry table, full tag match, accepted-fetch training, and replay-on-stall behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Folded-index ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only predictor that has produced a large bench improvement is the accepted-fetch instruction replay table, because it hides random hot-loop iStalls without branch-target lookup, predecode, or EX repair metadata. Follow-up replay changes that widened the table, repacked lines, warmed during backend stalls, or filtered redirect fills all regressed, so the next predictor step should preserve the same simple lookup semantics and avoid adding new storage depth or control paths.\n+\n+  The current 8-entry table is indexed directly by pc[4:2], so instructions separated by 32-byte strides always evict each other. CoreMark loop bodies and call-heavy code can easily contain hot PCs with that spacing, causing replay misses even after each instruction has been fetched successfully before.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the 8-entry accepted-fetch replay predictor exactly the same size and keep its fill-on-io_imemReady, replay-only-when-io_imemReady-is-low semantics, but replace the direct pc[4:2] index with a cheap folded hash such as pc[4:2] ^ pc[7:5]. Keep the existing full replay tag comparison so replay hits remain exact for the immutable instruction memory contract.\n+\n+  This targets direct-mapped conflict misses without the larger array, half-line muxing, backend warm cursor, redirect filter, branch predictor metadata, or next-PC target muxes that hurt prior predictor attempts. The hardware cost is only a few XOR gates feeding the existing 3-bit replay index, so any recovered hot-loop iStall hits should have a better chance of improving CoreMark fitness than another branch predictor or wider replay cache.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change the replay table index from direct pc[4:2] to a small folded PC hash while preserving the 8-entry table, full tag match, accepted-fetch training, and replay-on-stall behavior.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r14s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r14s2\n+title: \"Folded-index ifetch rep