{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778616570628,"sessionID":"ses_1e231c5d3ffenaXg59rkzuEz7i","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YFBismQNux9A2Lz8uXacOAbK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Victim-slot ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Branch-target predictors, RAS variants, countdown loop predictors, and\n+  replay-table capacity/hash changes have mostly regressed because extra PC\n+  muxing, EX repair metadata, or wider fetch routing cost more Fmax than they\n+  recovered in CoreMark cycles. The one predictor that improved this core is\n+  the accepted-fetch instruction replay table, which hides random hot-loop\n+  instruction stalls without predicting control flow.\n+\n+  The remaining plausible replay weakness is direct-mapped thrashing between a\n+  small number of hot PCs that share pc[4:2]. A single victim slot targets that\n+  specific failure mode without widening the primary table or changing the\n+  normal pc+4 fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the current 8-entry accepted-fetch replay predictor as the primary\n+  lookup, but add one fully-tagged victim replay slot. When an accepted fetch\n+  replaces a valid primary entry with a different tag, move the evicted tag and\n+  instruction into the victim slot. On io_imemReady=0, first check the indexed\n+  primary entry; if it misses, check the victim slot and replay its instruction\n+  on a tag hit. Do not predict branches or jumps, do not add predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata, and do not alter redirect handling.\n+\n+  This should recover iStall bubbles from two-way hot conflicts that the\n+  direct-mapped replay table cannot hold, while adding only one extra tag\n+  compare and one replay-data mux on the stalled-fetch path. It is narrower\n+  than the failed 16-entry, folded-index, line-packed, or warm-prefetch replay\n+  variants and preserves the immutable-instruction correctness argument.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry victim replay slot beside the existing 8-entry accepted-fetch table; fill it with evicted primary entries and consult it only on io_imemReady-low primary misses.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\n+title: \"Victim-slot ifetch replay predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Branch-target predictors, RAS variants, countdown loop predictors, and\n+  replay-table capacity/hash changes have mostly regressed because extra PC\n+  muxing, EX repair metadata, or wider fetch routing cost more Fmax than they\n+  recovered in CoreMark cycles. The one predictor that improved this core is\n+  the accepted-fetch instruction replay table, which hides random hot-loop\n+  instruction stalls without predicting control flow.\n+\n+  The remaining plausible replay weakness is direct-mapped thrashing between a\n+  small number of hot PCs that share pc[4:2]. A single victim slot targets that\n+  specific failure mode without widening the primary table or changing the\n+  normal pc+4 fetch path.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the current 8-entry accepted-fetch replay predictor as the primary\n+  lookup, but add one fully-tagged victim replay slot. When an accepted fetch\n+  replaces a valid primary entry with a different tag, move the evicted tag and\n+  instruction into the victim slot. On io_imemReady=0, first check the indexed\n+  primary entry; if it misses, check the victim slot and replay its instruction\n+  on a tag hit. Do not predict branches or jumps, do not add predicted-next-PC\n+  metadata, and do not alter redirect handling.\n+\n+  This should recover iStall bubbles from two-way hot conflicts that the\n+  direct-mapped replay table cannot hold, while adding only one extra tag\n+  compare and one replay-data mux on the stalled-fetch path. It is narrower\n+  than the failed 16-entry, folded-index, line-packed, or warm-prefetch replay\n+  variants and preserves the immutable-instruction correctness argument.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a one-entry victim replay slot beside the existing 8-entry accepted-fetch table; fill it with evicted primary entries and consult it only on io_imemReady-low primary misses.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r15s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r15s2\n+