{"type":"text","timestamp":1778594826503,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea7c4ffeh05RTYl7PVzD5j","part":{"id":"prt_e1c8344060015fOyHqajBJvkCv","messageID":"msg_e1c81f1fd0017Td5Ci7z6YWHDp","sessionID":"ses_1e37ea7c4ffeh05RTYl7PVzD5j","type":"text","text":"The cleanest predictor hypothesis is a low-cost IF predecode predictor: predict backward conditional branches and JALs to their target, then make EX redirect only on prediction mismatch. This targets CoreMark loop/control penalties without adding a stateful BTB/BHT on the Fmax-critical FPGA path.","time":{"start":1778594825222,"end":1778594826502},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_053154ea71fccde6016a033408f528819793479e3a229157a9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778594845797,"sessionID":"ses_1e37ea7c4ffeh05RTYl7PVzD5j","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_gbuZHvkblOxcDNTC5gbO5fqf","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static IF backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX and redirects on every taken control transfer. CoreMark spends much of its timed region in tight loops, so backward loop branches repeatedly pay a wrong-path bubble even though their target is statically knowable from the fetched instruction. A small static predictor can recover those bubbles while preserving the single-issue RVFI contract and avoiding a large Fmax hit.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add IF-stage predecode for conditional branches and JAL. Predict JAL as taken, predict conditional branches as taken only when the B-immediate is negative, and otherwise predict fall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, then change EX redirect generation to redirect only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction. This should remove most loop-back branch bubbles in CoreMark with only modest mux/add/sign-extension logic in the fetch path and no stateful predictor tables.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can identify prediction mismatches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL and backward conditional branch immediates, choose the predicted next PC, and emit prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the decoded instruction while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC and assert redirect only for mispredictions rather than every taken branch or jump.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Keep top-level control wiring consistent with redirect now meaning prediction miss, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static IF backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX and redirects on every taken control transfer. CoreMark spends much of its timed region in tight loops, so backward loop branches repeatedly pay a wrong-path bubble even though their target is statically knowable from the fetched instruction. A small static predictor can recover those bubbles while preserving the single-issue RVFI contract and avoiding a large Fmax hit.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add IF-stage predecode for conditional branches and JAL. Predict JAL as taken, predict conditional branches as taken only when the B-immediate is negative, and otherwise predict fall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, then change EX redirect generation to redirect only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction. This should remove most loop-back branch bubbles in CoreMark with only modest mux/add/sign-extension logic in the fetch path and no stateful predictor tables.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can identify prediction mismatches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL and backward conditional branch immediates, choose the predicted next PC, and emit prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the decoded instruction while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC and assert redirect only for mispredictions rather than every taken branch or jump.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Keep top-level control wiring consistent with redirect now meaning prediction miss, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r1s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r1s2\n+title: \"Static IF backward branch predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current five-stage core resolves all branches and jumps in EX and redirects on every taken control transfer. CoreMark spends much of its timed region in tight loops, so backward loop branches repeatedly pay a wrong-path bubble even though their target is statically knowable from the fetched instruction. A small static predictor can recover those bubbles while preserving the single-issue RVFI contract and avoiding a large Fmax hit.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add IF-stage predecode for conditional branches and JAL. Predict JAL as taken, predict conditional branches as taken only when the B-immediate is negative, and otherwise predict fall-through. Carry the predicted next PC through ID/EX, then change EX redirect generation to redirect only when the resolved next PC differs from the prediction. This should remove most loop-back branch bubbles in CoreMark with only modest mux/add/sign-extension logic in the fetch path and no stateful predictor tables.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 8\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX pipeline bundles so EX can identify prediction mismatches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL and backward conditional branch immediates, choose the predicted next PC, and emit prediction metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the decoded instruction while preserving existing stall and flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC and assert redirect only for mispredictions rather than every taken branch or jump.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Keep top-level control wiring consistent with redirect now meaning prediction miss, without changing the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n","additions":21,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":fals