{"type":"text","timestamp":1778596552680,"sessionID":"ses_1e3640253ffeuoshWxDIE4GW39","part":{"id":"prt_e1c9d9743001nLBCSb7Z4JkoLv","messageID":"msg_e1c9c6a34002sjN812JX53Pl7r","sessionID":"ses_1e3640253ffeuoshWxDIE4GW39","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor attempt failed because it put branch/JAL predecode on the `imem_data -> next_pc` fetch path. I’m writing a follow-up predictor hypothesis that keeps prediction lookup PC-indexed, so the fetch next-PC decision does not depend on decoding the just-returned instruction.","time":{"start":1778596550467,"end":1778596552678},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02fc3e661a258e08016a033ac637808196adb655a6ae27a835","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778596573867,"sessionID":"ses_1e3640253ffeuoshWxDIE4GW39","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Qg8HeuLjJ5aDHIIqWC7Q9Rwv","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"PC-indexed BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The previous static predictor recovered some loop-control bubbles but put\n+  instruction predecode and immediate generation on the fetch next-PC path,\n+  which is risky for Tang Nano 20K Fmax. CoreMark still has repeated taken\n+  loop branches and some direct/indirect jumps, so a predictor can help if the\n+  lookup path is driven only by the registered fetch PC rather than by\n+  io_imemData.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped PC-indexed BTB with a 2-bit taken counter and target\n+  per entry. IF predicts taken only on a tag hit with a taken counter and uses\n+  the stored target; otherwise it fetches pc+4. EX resolves the actual next PC,\n+  updates the table for branches and jumps, and redirects only when the resolved\n+  next PC differs from the carried prediction.\n+\n+  This should recover most steady-state CoreMark loop-back bubbles after warmup\n+  without the failed imem_data predecode critical path. The cost is a small\n+  PC-indexed LUT/register table and a compare/mux in IF, so the expected gain is\n+  modest but more Fmax-safe than static fetch predecode.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Carry predicted next-PC metadata from IF through ID/EX so EX can detect prediction mismatches without changing the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small PC-indexed BTB/BHT lookup and update interface, selecting either the stored predicted target or pc+4 without decoding io_imemData.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into the ID/EX bundle alongside the decoded instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC, generate predictor update information, and redirect only when the actual next PC mismatches the carried prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving the existing single-retirement RVFI port shape.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r2s2\n+title: \"PC-indexed BTB predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The previous static predictor recovered some loop-control bubbles but put\n+  instruction predecode and immediate generation on the fetch next-PC path,\n+  which is risky for Tang Nano 20K Fmax. CoreMark still has repeated taken\n+  loop branches and some direct/indirect jumps, so a predictor can help if the\n+  lookup path is driven only by the registered fetch PC rather than by\n+  io_imemData.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a small direct-mapped PC-indexed BTB with a 2-bit taken counter and target\n+  per entry. IF predicts taken only on a tag hit with a taken counter and uses\n+  the stored target; otherwise it fetches pc+4. EX resolves the actual next PC,\n+  updates the table for branches and jumps, and redirects only when the resolved\n+  next PC differs from the carried prediction.\n+\n+  This should recover most steady-state CoreMark loop-back bubbles after warmup\n+  without the failed imem_data predecode critical path. The cost is a small\n+  PC-indexed LUT/register table and a compare/mux in IF, so the expected gain is\n+  modest but more Fmax-safe than static fetch predecode.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 5\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Carry predicted next-PC metadata from IF through ID/EX so EX can detect prediction mismatches without changing the NRET=1 RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a small PC-indexed BTB/BHT lookup and update interface, selecting either the stored predicted target or pc+4 without decoding io_imemData.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch IF prediction metadata into the ID/EX bundle alongside the decoded instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC, generate predictor update information, and redirect only when the actual next PC mismatches the carried prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update signals between EX and IF while preserving the existing single-retirement RVFI port shape.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r2s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-a