{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778602405394,"sessionID":"ses_1e30c4a97ffeALfMMhd3mXamvF","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_6utUHBBPu9fu9CJHMm2OaPlh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Low-bit loop backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core regressed because full IF predecode,\n+  BTB tag/target lookup, hot redirect caching, and return prediction all added\n+  too much logic to the shallow fetch next-PC path. CoreMark still has repeated\n+  counted-loop backedges, but the predictor must be narrower than those failed\n+  designs to have any chance of improving fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry conditional-loop backedge predictor that learns only a hot\n+  taken backward conditional branch at EX and predicts it in IF using a small\n+  low-bit PC match, for example pc[7:2], plus a stored target. Do not predict\n+  JAL, JALR, forward branches, or returns, and do not keep a full tag, table,\n+  or saturating counters. Carry predicted next-PC metadata with the instruction\n+  so EX redirects only on mismatch and updates or clears the entry from the\n+  resolved branch.\n+\n+  This intentionally accepts occasional low-bit alias mispredictions because\n+  they are corrected precisely at EX, while making the IF critical-path addition\n+  much smaller than the previous predictor designs. If CoreMark has one dominant\n+  inner-loop backedge, the cycle savings may outweigh the small compare and mux;\n+  if aliasing or routing dominates, the hypothesis should fail cleanly without\n+  weakening RVFI or trap invariants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC and predicted-valid fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for precise EX mismatch detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single low-bit-matched backward-branch target entry, select the stored target on a hit, and update/clear it from EX resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the fetch prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the instruction without changing decoder legality defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC, redirect only when it differs from the carried prediction, and emit predictor update signals for taken backward conditional branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the predictor metadata and EX update path between IF, ID, and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Low-bit loop backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core regressed because full IF predecode,\n+  BTB tag/target lookup, hot redirect caching, and return prediction all added\n+  too much logic to the shallow fetch next-PC path. CoreMark still has repeated\n+  counted-loop backedges, but the predictor must be narrower than those failed\n+  designs to have any chance of improving fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry conditional-loop backedge predictor that learns only a hot\n+  taken backward conditional branch at EX and predicts it in IF using a small\n+  low-bit PC match, for example pc[7:2], plus a stored target. Do not predict\n+  JAL, JALR, forward branches, or returns, and do not keep a full tag, table,\n+  or saturating counters. Carry predicted next-PC metadata with the instruction\n+  so EX redirects only on mismatch and updates or clears the entry from the\n+  resolved branch.\n+\n+  This intentionally accepts occasional low-bit alias mispredictions because\n+  they are corrected precisely at EX, while making the IF critical-path addition\n+  much smaller than the previous predictor designs. If CoreMark has one dominant\n+  inner-loop backedge, the cycle savings may outweigh the small compare and mux;\n+  if aliasing or routing dominates, the hypothesis should fail cleanly without\n+  weakening RVFI or trap invariants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC and predicted-valid fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for precise EX mismatch detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single low-bit-matched backward-branch target entry, select the stored target on a hit, and update/clear it from EX resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the fetch prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the instruction without changing decoder legality defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC, redirect only when it differs from the carried prediction, and emit predictor update signals for taken backward conditional branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the predictor metadata and EX update path between IF, ID, and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Low-bit loop backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core regressed because full IF predecode,\n+  BTB tag/target lookup, hot redirect caching, and return prediction all added\n+  too much logic to the shallow fetch next-PC path. CoreMark still has repeated\n+  counted-loop backedges, but the predictor must be narrower than those failed\n+  designs to have any chance of improving fitness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry conditional-loop backedge predictor that learns only a hot\n+  taken backward conditional branch at EX and predicts it in IF using a small\n+  low-bit PC match, for example pc[7:2], plus a stored target. Do not predict\n+  JAL, JALR, forward branches, or returns, and do not keep a full tag, table,\n+  or saturating counters. Carry predicted next-PC metadata with the instruction\n+  so EX redirects only on mismatch and updates or clears the entry from the\n+  resolved branch.\n+\n+  This intentionally accepts occasional low-bit alias mispredictions because\n+  they are corrected precisely at EX, while making the IF critical-path addition\n+  much smaller than the previous predictor designs. If CoreMark has one dominant\n+  inner-loop backedge, the cycle savings may outweigh the small compare and mux;\n+  if aliasing or routing dominates, the hypothesis should fail cleanly without\n+  weakening RVFI or trap invariants.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted next-PC and predicted-valid fields to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for precise EX mismatch detection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single low-bit-matched backward-branch target entry, select the stored target on a hit, and update/clear it from EX resolution.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Latch the fetch prediction metadata into ID/EX alongside the instruction without changing decoder legality defaults.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Resolve the actual next PC, redirect only when it differs from the carried prediction, and emit predictor update signals for taken backward conditional branches.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the predictor metadata and EX update path between IF, ID, and EX while preserving the nret=1 RVFI port contract.\"\n","additions":38,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r5s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778602405387,"end":1778602405392}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0e70af393fb3d0b1016a03518ea5dc8193b5e753027873344b"}},"id":"prt_e1cf6958c001FbBGuuxEdtxHQw","sessionID":"ses_1e30c4a97ffeALfMMhd3mXamvF","messageID":"msg_e1cf603bd001KWhj4YhIEk0KKI"}}
