{"type":"text","timestamp":1778603961420,"sessionID":"ses_1e2f21c23ffeF58pltgYDCObgC","part":{"id":"prt_e1d0eaba900114C0YjIZQ41aF3","messageID":"msg_e1d0e4ee7001PoufVIauu445d0","sessionID":"ses_1e2f21c23ffeF58pltgYDCObgC","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor failures all added fetch next-PC work. I’m writing a predictor hypothesis that moves prediction/early redirect out of IF and into decode, reducing branch penalty without a PC-indexed lookup or imem-data-to-PC target path.","time":{"start":1778603961257,"end":1778603961419},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_028f156259dfb422016a0357b927a8819090766f91cb1e5889","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778604130736,"sessionID":"ses_1e2f21c23ffeF58pltgYDCObgC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_O8tRV0UoFuUDvmuxeNsMfnbk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Countdown loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered plausible branch bubbles but regressed because\n+  they put instruction predecode, PC tag compares, target-table lookup, or return\n+  decode directly on the shallow fetch next-PC path. CoreMark still has repeated\n+  counted-loop backedges, so the remaining promising predictor angle is one that\n+  avoids both imem_data decode and PC-indexed table lookup during fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry countdown loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\n+  backward conditional branches. When EX sees a taken backedge, record its target\n+  and the small instruction-distance from target to branch, then arm a fetch-side\n+  down-counter after redirecting to the loop target. IF decrements the counter\n+  only on real fetch advances; when it expires, it predicts the next PC as the\n+  recorded target without doing any PC tag compare or instruction predecode.\n+\n+  Carry predicted-next metadata with each fetched instruction so EX can validate\n+  every prediction against the resolved next PC, redirect on mismatch, and retrain\n+  or disable the countdown entry cleanly. This intentionally targets one stable\n+  inner-loop backedge and accepts occasional precise mispredictions, trading a\n+  tiny counter-zero test and target mux for avoiding the failed predictor logic\n+  that previously lengthened the IF critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for precise EX validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire loop-predictor update and prediction-validation signals between IF and EX without changing the NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the single-entry countdown loop predictor state, fetch-advance countdown, and predicted-target PC selection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Carry prediction metadata from the fetch payload into the ID/EX register across stalls and flushes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate predicted next PCs, redirect only on mismatch, and train or disable the countdown predictor from resolved backward branches.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,37 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r6s2\n+title: \"Countdown loop predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts recovered plausible branch bubbles but regressed because\n+  they put instruction predecode, PC tag compares, target-table lookup, or return\n+  decode directly on the shallow fetch next-PC path. CoreMark still has repeated\n+  counted-loop backedges, so the remaining promising predictor angle is one that\n+  avoids both imem_data decode and PC-indexed table lookup during fetch.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry countdown loop predictor trained only by resolved taken\n+  backward conditional branches. When EX sees a taken backedge, record its target\n+  and the small instruction-distance from target to branch, then arm a fetch-side\n+  down-counter after redirecting to the loop target. IF decrements the counter\n+  only on real fetch advances; when it expires, it predicts the next PC as the\n+  recorded target without doing any PC tag compare or instruction predecode.\n+\n+  Carry predicted-next metadata with each fetched instruction so EX can validate\n+  every prediction against the resolved next PC, redirect on mismatch, and retrain\n+  or disable the countdown entry cleanly. This intentionally targets one stable\n+  inner-loop backedge and accepts occasional precise mispredictions, trading a\n+  tiny counter-zero test and target mux for avoiding the failed predictor logic\n+  that previously lengthened the IF critical path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX bundles for precise EX validation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire loop-predictor update and prediction-validation signals between IF and EX without changing the NRET=1 RVFI port set.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add the single-entry countdown loop predictor state, fetch-advance countdown, and predicted-target PC selection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Carry prediction metadata from the fetch payload into the ID/EX register across stalls and flushes.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate predicted next PCs, redirect only on mismatch, and train or disable the countdown predictor from resolved backward branches.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r6s2.yaml","type":