{"type":"text","timestamp":1778605353577,"sessionID":"ses_1e2de84a3ffe8Dt45znyHyo7UD","part":{"id":"prt_e1d23e419001A7bRzyC8Tsppw4","messageID":"msg_e1d239187001So3w2yaL4rKPRk","sessionID":"ses_1e2de84a3ffe8Dt45znyHyo7UD","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now with a JAL-only decode-stage predictor, keeping the change scoped to `cores/bench` and using only `rtl/...` paths in the YAML.","time":{"start":1778605351962,"end":1778605353572},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d2c4ba492ceb38b016a035d27de708194a4f61710e14028e8","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778605377983,"sessionID":"ses_1e2de84a3ffe8Dt45znyHyo7UD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_zwckxsCDvtpAGWvtXI6ddbnN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage direct JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core regressed because they added BTB, RAS,\n+  branch-predecode, or countdown repair logic to the shallow fetch/control path.\n+  The remaining low-risk control-flow opportunity is direct JAL: its target is\n+  known from the fetched instruction and PC, it is always taken when legal, and\n+  it does not require a branch comparator, history table, or return stack.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Predict only legal aligned direct JAL instructions one stage earlier, in ID.\n+  When ID is actually advancing and sees a non-JALR JAL with an aligned target,\n+  update the fetch PC to the J-immediate target while still allowing the JAL\n+  itself to enter ID/EX. Carry a one-bit early-JAL prediction marker into EX so\n+  EX still produces the correct RVFI pc_wdata and link result but suppresses the\n+  redundant redirect for that already-predicted JAL. Leave conditional branches,\n+  JALR, misaligned JAL targets, and all dynamic predictor state on the existing\n+  EX-resolution path.\n+\n+  This recovers one redirect bubble for direct calls and unconditional jumps in\n+  CoreMark without a fetch-side table, PC tag compare, return decoder, or branch\n+  immediate predictor. The expected gain is modest but more Fmax-safe than the\n+  prior predictor designs because the new PC feedback is JAL-only and can be\n+  gated by ID advance rather than placed on every fetch next-PC decision.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a single ID/EX metadata bit indicating that a direct JAL was already redirected in decode.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Detect legal aligned direct JAL when ID is valid and advancing, compute its target, request an early PC redirect, and latch the metadata bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a decode-redirect PC update path that does not squash the current fetched instruction; keep EX redirects highest priority and preserve existing flush behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"For early-predicted direct JAL, keep link/pc_next/RVFI behavior but suppress the redundant EX redirect while preserving misaligned-target traps and JALR handling.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the ID-stage direct-JAL redirect request and target into IF, gated by existing stall/flush conditions and lower priority than EX redirects.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r7s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,38 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r7s2\n+title: \"Decode-stage direct JAL predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts on this core regressed because they added BTB, RAS,\n+  branch-predecode, or countdown repair logic to the shallow fetch/control path.\n+  The remaining low-risk control-flow opportunity is direct JAL: its target is\n+  known from the fetched instruction and PC, it is always taken wh