{"type":"text","timestamp":1778607047628,"sessionID":"ses_1e2c4ebf4ffephwG5Nu2Rm3n8Y","part":{"id":"prt_e1d3dc1ed001QvpJOmxqnyx3mO","messageID":"msg_e1d3b6cc6001zchydSQ4vfpQv2","sessionID":"ses_1e2c4ebf4ffephwG5Nu2Rm3n8Y","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently regressed when lookup/decode fed the fetch next-PC path. I’m writing a narrower hypothesis that shifts the lookup one cycle earlier and uses only registered prediction bits on the PC update path.","time":{"start":1778607047149,"end":1778607047625},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_015097921c41a96f016a0363c701bc8190941c35acfe1ecb18","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778607071379,"sessionID":"ses_1e2c4ebf4ffephwG5Nu2Rm3n8Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_h93fT3HsztXWrMD54OktmwUY","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Registered lookahead backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts found exploitable CoreMark loop control flow but lost\n+  more Fmax than they recovered because branch predecode, BTB lookup, tag\n+  compares, or return recognition landed directly on the shallow fetch next-PC\n+  path. The remaining promising predictor angle is to keep the PC update path\n+  driven only by registered state while still learning one hot loop backedge.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a single-entry conditional-backedge predictor with a one-cycle lookahead\n+  lookup. When EX resolves a taken backward conditional branch, store its branch\n+  PC, the preceding sequential PC, and the target. While fetching normally, IF\n+  compares the current PC against the stored preceding PC and registers whether\n+  the next sequential instruction is the learned branch; on the following cycle,\n+  the PC mux uses only that registered predict-valid bit and registered target.\n+\n+  This should recover steady-state bubbles for a dominant CoreMark loop branch\n+  without putting a BTB table, current-PC tag compare, instruction predecode, or\n+  branch-immediate adder on the same-cycle fetch next-PC path. EX still carries\n+  predicted-next metadata, redirects precisely on mismatch, and disables the\n+  entry on loop exit or aliasing, preserving RVFI order, trap behavior, and the\n+  NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact predicted-next-PC metadata to IF/ID and ID/EX so EX can validate a registered lookahead prediction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Implement a single-entry lookahead backedge predictor using registered predict-valid/target state on the PC update path and EX-trained branch metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate prediction metadata through the ID/EX register without changing decode legality or RVFI source fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Suppress redirects on correct predictions, redirect on mismatches, and emit taken/not-taken conditional-branch update signals for the IF predictor.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire predictor update and prediction metadata between IF, ID, and EX while preserving the single-channel RVFI port contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_branch_predictor.py\n+    description: \"Add focused cocotb coverage for correct loop prediction, loop-exit misprediction repair, and stalls around predicted branches.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_xhigh-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,39 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Registered lookahead backedge predictor\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  Prior predictor attempts found exploitable CoreMark loop control flow but lost\n+  more Fmax than they recovered because branch predecode, BTB lookup, tag\n+  compares, or return recognition landed directly on the shallow fetch next-PC