{"type":"text","timestamp":1778608931395,"sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c356ffeKwI3WRIPgNGjbR","part":{"id":"prt_e1d5a7838001auLwqgw7FJsFg0","messageID":"msg_e1d58a90d001xceKy7jDJmR3UP","sessionID":"ses_1e2a7c356ffeKwI3WRIPgNGjbR","type":"text","text":"Prior predictor attempts consistently regressed when they put PC lookup, instruction predecode, or prediction-repair metadata on the normal fetch next-PC path. I’m going to write a narrower predictor hypothesis that targets taken-redirect bubbles by replaying a cached branch-target instruction only on an actual EX redirect, keeping the steady-state fetch path unchanged.","time":{"start":1778608928824,"end":1778608931394},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c90a2b67e9ab1c9016a036b20aa688193b0303ebcaa422f9e","phase":"commentary"}}}}
